description:
"I actually don't know if I even owned a Barbie." Margot Robbie may have not been obsessed with the dolls as a child, but there was one thing that she was extremely keen on: the Barbie Dreamhouse. From constructing her fold-out house as a 5-year-old to seeing a life-size version come to life right before her eyes, Margot Robbie truly manifested her Barbie dreams. Margot breaks down her entire process for the 'Barbie' movie, from the mental preparation for the role, working alongside Greta Gerwig and Ryan Gosling on set, the fabulous pink wardrobe and so much more.

SAG-AFTRA members are currently on strike; as part of the strike, union actors are not promoting their film and TV projects. This video was conducted prior to the strike.

description:
Apple said it could remove services such as FaceTime and iMessage from users in the UK rather than complying with the UK government's proposed security rules. 

The UK government is seeking to update the Investigatory Powers Act (IPA) 2016.

It wants messaging services to clear security features with the Home Office before releasing them to customers.

The act lets the Home Office demand security features are disabled, without telling the public. Under the update, this would have to be immediate.

description:
'Exploring London's Hidden Medieval Metropolis'

If you were asked to picture London during the Middle Ages, you might think of The White Tower, Westminster Abbey or Guildhall - some of the capital‚Äôs most famous landmarks. But scratch beneath the surface and you‚Äôll find there are lots more clues to this medieval metropolis.

In the second episode of 'Hidden London', London tour guide Katie Wignall seeks out the London of the Middle Ages - a city of narrow streets and soaring spires, almost completely destroyed by the Great Fire of 1666‚Ä¶ and the Blitz during the Second World War. But despite the devastation and centuries of development, not all of that city is lost. 

Katie start her tour at the London Charterhouse, which has been home to many significant moments in London's history since 1371. It has been a monastery, grand mansion, boys school and an almshouse, which it remains to this day. More recently, Charterhouse square was dug up as part of London's cross rail construction and a mass burial dating back to the Black Death in the 14th Century was discovered. 

Next, Katie visits part of the Roman Wall which used to surround the old city. She then touches upon the history of London Bridge which has undergone reconstruction twice in the few centuries and looks very different from the heavily built upon medieval bridge - home to some of the wealthiest citizens at the time. 

After passing several significant medieval palaces, rivers, churches, stones and clinks, Katie arrives at her final destination - St John's Priory. Headquarters of the Knights Hospitaller, the monks who lived there in the Middle Ages took vows of poverty, chastity, and obedience, and were expected to fight on crusade in the Holy Land if called upon.

description:
hello friends (‚ïØ‚ñΩ‚ï∞ )
i welcome you to another study session! let's be productive together for a few hours :))
u can read a lil study guide below!~~üåü

i filmed these during my finals season! i hope you enjoy them & can have a productive time here, and most importantly, enjoy the shots of ollie peacefully sleeping.
i tried to lower the volume of the loud sounds (i get in the zone and forget to be more careful handling materials) and cut around camera noises, however because of the length of the video, i always miss some and it makes me want to delete the video, never post it! but i'm curbing my perfectionism this year ‚â°(‚ñîÔπè‚ñî)‚â° & i promised a no music swm to viewers, so here it is. next one will be better, pinky promise. most of all, i just hope these can be a wonderful companion to those feeling less inspired to keep going.
i hope you have a wonderful weekend/week ahead of u ü•∫ best of luck with all your studies!!~‚≠ê i hope you're healthy and strong. a big big hug xx
lots of love,
maria
üíóüêª

‚úßÔΩ•Ôæü how it works: ‚úßÔΩ•Ôæü
there are four study sessions, 50 mins each, with three 10 min breaks included.
focus as best as you can during your study session because we'll be resting in just a bit. it will get easier the more you do it, as your brain can be trained to focus for longer periods of time as you study consistently, so don't give up! you can do this :-) 
aditionally, because this is a no music SWM, if you feel like it, you can always add your own playlists in the background or lofi streams, for example.

‚úßÔΩ•Ôæü at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)

‚úßÔΩ•Ôæü during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

‚úßÔΩ•Ôæü at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can repeat this video!

you're set to go! ‚ô°

(Íàç·¥óÍàç) stay cozy!

description:
i built my first ever gaming pc a while ago, but I had been too lazy to edit the video. finally got around to it a month later. enjoy!

follow me on social media:
üåøInstagram: @nyssaqueen
üåøTwitter: @nyssaqj
üåøSpotify: https://open.spotify.com/user/nyssaqueen
subscribe for more: https://www.youtube.com/c/nyssaQueen

DISCLAIMER: as the title says this is my first ever build so i am not a pro at this whatsoever and therefore this is not a tutorial on how to build a computer, as i am still learning myself. i also make a lot of mistakes, as i talk about in the video, so feel free to let me know how i can improve, just be kind about it please :)

PC Parts List:
‚Üí case: lian li dynamic evo
‚Üí motherboard: asus rog strict b550-a
‚Üí memory: t-force xtreem 3600mhz (2x16gb)
‚Üí cpu: ryzen 7 5800x
‚Üí psu: corsair rmx 850w
‚Üí gpu: geforce rtx 3080ti fe
‚Üí storage: samsung 980 pro m.2 1t
‚Üí fans: lian li sl120
‚Üí cooler: nzxt z73 aio
‚Üí custom cable: lian li strimer plus 24 pin
‚Üí wifi card: ubit ac wifi card 1200mbps
‚Üí usb splitter: rocketek 9pin usb header male 1 to 4 female extension 

PC Part Picker: https://pcpartpicker.com/list/TMpGLs

Peripherals:
‚Üí monitor: lg 32ul500-w 4k monitor
‚Üí keyboard: womier k66, brown switches
‚Üí mouse pad: razer goliathus extended chroma
‚Üí mouse: razer viper ultralight ambidextrous
‚Üí custom keycaps: razer phantom keycaps

**overall this build cost me $2658.36, not including the peripherals. but that's only because i bought almost everything on sale and used every student and other discount known to man. but realistically this build would easily cost well over $3k. so i am very fortunate to have been able to get all the parts i wanted for the prices that i did**

description:
Sul sul friends!
Welcome to Bilbo Baggins's cozy hobbit hole build in Sims 4! 
As a Lord of the Rings fan, building a hobbit hole was a must-do on my list. This unique take on the classic hobbit home actually takes inspiration from the acorn shape, half-buried in the ground, with massive tree growing on top of the roof, making it fully secluded hideaway. 
As usual, I kept the exterior simple yet charming, and covered the roof with all kinds of bushes that help it blend into the surroundings seamlessly.
Enjoy the video and thank you for watching!

1:18 Interior
7:28 Landscape and Finishing

Gallery ID: themossysim

For this build, I did not use any custom content or mods. However, I did make use of the 'moveobjects' cheat. Please make sure to enable this cheat before placing the lot.

All information about this house you can find in the video :)

Technical Details: No CC used! The paintings in the build are No CC Paintings (Gallery Art). These are NOT marked as CC in the gallery and can therefore be used by console players. These paintings were done by a Sim at the easel!

Download Available from May 15, 2023
Sims 4 Gallery ID: xXSarina_27xX
Tray Files: https://lnk.bio/jIs4
You will find the houses there under the category "Tray Files" if you scroll down.

I use the Tool Mod from Twisted Mexi for my Sims 4 builds! You will find hints in the video, in addition, the video says which Tool Mod values I have used. Unfortunately, this mod can only be used on the PC. BUT to download my houses, you must NOT have installed the mod. All objects are downloaded in the same position as you can see in the video. This means that Pc AND console players can use my houses. You only need the same packs of game that I used.

In this The Sims 4 Stop Motion Speedbuild + Tips & Tricks video, I show you the building process and the interior of the Sims 4 house "Modern Luxury Barn". In the video you will find as always hints of the used packs and tool mod values. The complete build is No CC and contains No CC paintings. Hey there, fellow crafters and DIY enthusiasts! Join me on this exciting journey as I completely transform my living room into aDark Academia - ish haven by myself. From wall painting to wood flooring and DIY home decor, this video has it all!
In this creative adventure, I'll show you step-by-step how to give your living space a touch of elegance and mystery, all while staying on a budget. Prepare to be inspired as we dive into the details of crafting and decorating, with a sprinkle of humor along the way.

Watch as I turn ordinary walls into something more elegant using simple and affordable materials. From bookshelves to ancient scrolls, we'll create a library-like atmosphere that'll make you feel like you're stepping into a magical world. Mostly because I got all this furniture for free.
Next, get ready to roll up your sleeves and embark on a DIY flooring adventure. I'll guide you through the process of transforming your room with stunning wood flooring that adds warmth and sophistication to those ugly tiles. Don't worry if you're new to DIY projects ‚Äì I'll share some handy tips and tricks to make the process smooth and enjoyable.
But wait, there's more! We can't forget about the little details that make a big difference. I'll show you how to craft beautiful and budget-friendly home decor pieces that kinda complement the Dark Academia aesthetic. 
So, whether you're a crafty beginner or a seasoned DIY pro, this video is packed with ideas and inspiration to help you create the Dark Academia living room of your dreams. Get ready to unleash your creativity, all while embracing the enchanting world of crafting and fashion.

description:
Prepare to be blown away by our most ambitious crafting endeavor yet! In this extraordinary YouTube video, we unveil the art of next-level creativity by transforming any glass bottle into a stunning vintage vase.

No bottle is off-limits as we embark on this upcycling adventure. Witness the magic of imagination as we take ordinary glass bottles and elevate them into timeless pieces of art with our expert techniques and ingenuity.

Our step-by-step tutorial will guide you through the intricacies of glass manipulation, showcasing cutting-edge methods that turn discarded bottles into works of art with unparalleled charm. Be amazed by the artistry of shaping, painting, and adding unique embellishments that give each vase a character of its own.

This isn't just about crafting; it's about making a statement for sustainable living and eco-consciousness. By reusing glass bottles, we celebrate the beauty of repurposing and showcase how creativity can merge with environmental responsibility.

Whether you're a seasoned crafter or just beginning to explore the world of DIY, this video promises to take your creativity to new heights. From elegant decoupage to exquisite glass etching, you'll discover an array of techniques that inspire you to see the potential in every glass bottle.

Join our thriving community of art enthusiasts by hitting the like button, sharing this video with fellow creatives, and subscribing to our channel for regular doses of crafting inspiration and innovative DIY decoration projects.

description:
Hello Everyone and thank you for joining me on my second visit to Michael's. I thought that they would add more decor to their new fall collections and I wanted to bring you along. 

After visiting another Michael's location, you will see that they added many new items to their fall collections with beautiful colourful pumpkins and their fall stems were beyond amazing...so many choices and decorating ideas! 

I saw a few new gorgeous wreaths, multiple stems and picks from pumpkins, acorns and floral and the addition of stunning serve ware with beautiful fall designs for your gatherings.

So many great ideas, I was so inspired and ready to decorate for fall but not quite! ;) I'm waiting patiently for Michael's fall sale to pick up a few tings to add to my growing fall decor collection.

I hope you got some motivation and great ideas today on what's new at Michael's for 2023 fall season for your home.

Hello and welcome if you're new and please consider subscribing, give me a thumbs up and share with your friends...I would love it if you would join my YouTube family.

Thank you for watching and hope you enjoy!
xoxo Diana

Pollack Roe Breakfast Bowl

description:
J. Robert Oppenheimer forever changed the course of history. He may be the most important physicist to have ever lived. Part of this video is sponsored by Wren. Offset your carbon footprint on Wren: ‚Äãhttps://www.wren.co/start/veritasium1 For the first 100 people who sign up, I will personally pay for the first month of your subscription!

If you want to learn more about Oppeheimer, I strongly recommend the book ‚ÄúAmerican Prometheus‚Äù By Kai Bird and Martin Sherwin. It is a remarkable book, very much deserving of the Pulitzer prize it received.

If you‚Äôre looking for a molecular modeling kit, try Snatoms ‚Äì a kit I invented where the atoms snap together magnetically ‚Äì https://ve42.co/SnatomsV

‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ

title: Thrift With Me - Exciting Thrift Haul #2

description:
We all found treasures at this AMAZING Goodwill and met a friend on the way out! Goodwill Huntington Beach was restocking.... look at all the treasures I found!

Hello Everyone! Its Tiffany with Thrifting Vegas. I shop at thrift stores, estate sales, garage sales and discount stores for items I can resell for a profit on online platforms like eBay, Poshmark and Offer-Up.
Join me as I hit Goodwill Huntington Beach with Danni @TheNICHELady and my parents for a Sunday morning shop. The store was packed full of goodies and we found plently of treasure, and even some 50% off tags!  Learn what to bolo for and what to leave on the shelf and why. I found a Talavera Mexican Pottery saucer, a gorgeous pottery vase, the biggest, heaviest Snowman and Santa chimineas I've EVER seen, a modern MCM mirror, a vintage display cabinet and an AMAZING uranium glass pedestal cake stand!!!!  Stay to see how we fit it all in the car,  meet Jamie @MidCenturyWasted and for a quick trip into Corona Salvation Army on the way home! Don't forget the new dates for our October Vintage Market Booth.... and watch my haul featuring Bandit the cat, where I show you everything I found, what I paid and what I expect to get for it......so, lets go thrifting!

Please like, subscribe and hit the bell to get a notification when I upload a new video!

If you are interested in purchasing an item from my haul, please DM me on Instagram; or email me at ThriftingVegas.Tiffany@gmail.com

We would love to see you at our booth at the Fantastic Vintage Market within the Fantastic Indoor Swapmeet at 1717 S Decatur Bl, Las Vegas! The Market takes place every third weekend of the month. The next sale is in our NEW BOOTH LOCATION Friday, Saturday and Sunday, October  15, 16 and 17 from 10am to 6pm.

description:
Its Goodwill's Christmas 50% off Seasonal Tags Sale .....and there was HARDLY ANYONE THERE....
Hello Everyone! Its Tiffany with Thrifting Vegas. I shop at thrift stores, estate sales, garage sales and discount stores for items I can resell for a profit on online platforms like eBay, Poshmark and Offer-Up.
Its Christmas Eve and there were just a very few people shopping for last minute treasures....Goodwill was almost deserted!  Thrift with me as I show you what to bolo and what to leave there on the shelf and why. I found some amazing treasures including a Frankoma Deviled Egg plate, a Williams Sonoma Bowl, a brood of Tonala Ducklings, an Onlyx Pedestal Bowl,  a Fitz and Floyd Tissue Box Holder, a Quarry Critters cat and a Kosta Boda Frutteria Glass Pear!!!  Don't miss the latest footage of our brand new house. The first floor flooring has been demoed and the guest bathroom completely gutted.... its ready for something new!  Stay to watch my haul featuring Bandit the cat, where I show you everything I found, what I paid and what I expect to get for it.......so, LET'S GO THRIFTING!!!

Please like, subscribe and hit the bell to get a notification when I upload a new video!

description:
Hello Everyone!

I'm so glad that you can join me today for this thrifting adventure as I wanted to introduce and share a video like this for some time.

When I go thrifting I'm usually looking for vintage and antique decor items to decorate my home.  I love the thrill of the hunt and also appreciate that these pieces can be economical and certainly unique.

You will find a few vintage pieces in today's video and the artwork was amazing, I wanted to take many home with me! Please stay to the end as I share an awesome small thrift haul.

So let me know if I missed something that I should have taken home and have you found a unique decor item that you're still obsessing about? Would love to hear back from you. :)

Please consider subscribing if you like this type of content as I'm slowly curating my home with these types of decor finds.

Thank you for watching.  Enjoy!
xoxo Diana

description:
Fairy Cottage Renovation and Decoration

Hi! My name is Johanna. Welcome to my channel and my dream home! In this video I will share with you the process of bringing back to life an abandoned place and house that belong to my family, renovating the stove and a room of my new home, decorating it and transforming it in a cottage fit for a fairy. 

This channel is about house restoring and decorating, gardening, cooking and growing one's food, rural life or countryside life in a small village, crafting useful and beautiful things that make life in the countryside easier and more enjoyable. Join me on my everyday life adventures as countryside life besides being peaceful and beautiful, can be a real challenge sometimes!

If you've enjoyed watching the first video I've uploaded here, please do subscribe and share it with a dear friend. A big thank you to all of you that will help my new channel reach more people! Happy Holidays to all of you!

description:
Finally posting this dress video!! 

This video is so late. I got super busy and did not have time to finish editing it. Our power went out the day I had set aside to work on it, so it had to wait. 

I am so proud of how well this dress came together. It is incredibly beautiful, and I love it to the moon and back. Its romantic, long and flowy, comfortable, no fuss, and all around perfect. I was working on a knit shawl to match this dress, but, ahem, problems arose. 

If you have any questions about the construction of this dress, feel free to ask! 
Also, I did go to the eye dr, and I have a diagnosis, and I've been on meds since 6/29...because that's how delayed this video is. Which I do feel bad about. My 40th was last week, and it was just crazy busy. 

The bodice pattern I used was: McCalls M7654  https://simplicity.com/mccalls/pdm7654
I also used 1/4" elastic. 

Music by Motion Array

description:
Check out my 3D printed fractals! http://www.shapeways.com/shops/3Dfractals
Fractal animation made with Mandelbulb3D. I originally designed it for Bryan Alvarez from UC Berkeley, for a TEDx talk about his Human Atlas project, to illustrate his initial dream about the beauty of living systems, hence the name of the video. This particular fractal a hybrid Julia set where many parameters are being animated: the fractal paramaters themselves, the Julia seed, the colors, and of course the camera position. One could say it's not 3D, but many-many-D!

Want to see it for real? Buy 3D fractals printed in 3D : http://www.shapeways.com/shops/3Dfractals

Music courtesy of Zzzzra - Pneuma - filtre lent.

description:
In this video I upcycle, repurpose, and combine several thrifted finds from estate sales, thrift stores, an architectural salvage clearance sale, an Amazon pallet clearance center, and curb finds! I update a 1990‚Äôs country floor lamp, wicker suitcase from Mexico, and wooden canister set; turn an old desk drawer and thrifted metal legs into a unique side table, turn another old desk drawer into wall storage; create framed art with thrifted frames, notecards, wallpaper samples, and needlepoint. I repurpose an old clock frame and a trashed pedestal table base. I use a toy buggy as a succulent planter, turn a ceramic bird votive candle holder into an adorable pin cushion, and much more! I hope this video provides you with lots of creative inspiration.

The Goodwill outlet is one of my favorite places to find home decor on a budget. If you are trying to decorate your home and don‚Äôt want to break the bank, I love how far you can stretch your dollar at the Goodwill outlet.

Another thing I love about it is that something from Pottery Barn, Restoration Hardware, or West Elm is not going to cost any more than an item laying right next to it from the dollar store. 

If you‚Äôre new to my channel here welcome! If you are interested in DIY, interior design and decorating, or would like to see more shopping halls, check out my channel, and don‚Äôt forget to hit that subscribe button so you don‚Äôt miss future videos.

description:
Restoration Hardware has stunning decor...at prices that can stun you!  So why not dupe them for a fraction of the cost?  And all of the satisfaction of a DIY project!

The RH Indonesian Currency Disk is a gorgeous large piece and it's simple design is perfect for a dupe project.  In this video I start with foam board from the Dollar Tree, add a some drywall mud, paint and a whole lot of time and I end up with a large, inexpensive, high end dup.

D√©cor trends change all the time.  How we use our spaces changes too.  And I agree, there are items that should be splurged on to make sure you get quality and longevity.  This is why it's such a great idea to save on d√©cor pieces with dupes and DIYs.  Save money in one area to spend it somewhere else.

This d√©cor piece is part of my dining room project.  I know in the future, I'm completely redecorating the dining room; new furniture, wall trim, new art, the works.  But for now, I want it to at least look presentable.  So instead of splurging, I'm saving, duping and DIYing!  Remember to subscribe and ring the notification bell to see all the high end low budget dining room decorating ideas!

description:
#Howtomakewreaths #flowerwreath #DIYcrafts #wreathdiy #wreathtutorial #christmasdecor  

Who doesn't love a little sparkle in their life? Today's wreath is a poinsettia made from a sparkly gold poly deco mesh alternating with white poly burlap mesh.  It's so easy to make and can be recreated in many different colors! Enjoy!!!

I bought my mesh for this project from:
Craftoutlet.com

Supplies:
One roll of 10" white poly burlap mesh 
One roll of 10"  window pane poly deco mesh (in "champagne")
One roll of 10" lime green poly burlap mesh for leaves (optional)
8" zip ties
#5 plastic mesh for wreath center
8" Dollar Tree wire wreath frame
6 gold plastic bulb ornaments (1.5" diameter)
floral wire

description:
WOW!  In this DIY video, I am going to take you step by step and show you how you can create your very own, one of a kind, boho patchwork coat.  This is not as hard as it looks.  This luscious coat started as a thrifted dress and was embellished with pieces from a vintage blanket, and patches made from blazers and a skirt.  We will also do some creative cutting and sewing to make flared cuff sleeves and pockets.  Even the button closure is upcycled (no button hole making...yay!).  I'm sure you will find this a very rewarding project whether you make this for yourself or you upcycle fashion to sell.

description:
As suggested I created an angel using tomato cage. This was a long project but in the end I was truly happy with it and how beautiful it looks. I hope you will enjoy it.
ITEMS I USED TO MAKE ANGEL......
33'' tomato cage
2 rolls of 21 inch wide by 30 ft deco mesh (your color choice)
3 rolls of 6 inch wide by 5 yds deco mesh (your color choice)
1 roll of 10 inch wide by 10 yd deco mesh (opt and your color choice)
1 styro foam ball 6 inch diameter (5.7 inch on label) 
chenille stems or floral wire
string of 200 lights
1 string 10 lights and batteries
1 small wreath for halo (or use chenille to form halo)
1 1/2 inch wide ribbon 
2 inch ribbon
decorative items such as flowers, pine, greenery, any additional ribbons, berries, plastic snow flakes or other ornaments that you would like to add to your angel. :)

floral pins, scissors, wire cutters, glue gun with glue sticks or E600 glue.

description:
Good morning! In today's crafting adventure I will show you how to make this yarn and ribbon Valentines Day Heart Wreath. A beautiful Valentine's Day wreath that is budget friendly using mostly Dollar Tree items and is easy to make. I will share with you each step in the creation process and show you just how easy it is to make this unique Dollar Tree Valentines Day yarn and ribbon wreath. Your going to love this Valentine's Day craft!

I originally learned about this technique of making a wreath from creator Nathalie Creates Crafts,  here is her link https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCDvf0DYkDhZ4dzr8FwYrSBA
Thank you Nathalie!

Please help to support my channel, Simply by hitting the like button, leaving some love in the comment section, and hitting subscribe to join the crafting family really does help my channel get noticed by You Tube. description:
How To Paint Fabric Furniture The Easy Way / A Step by Step Guide
Hi there,
Are you looking to transform your old, tired fabric furniture into something new and beautiful? Look no further! In this step-by-step tutorial, we'll show you how to paint fabric furniture the easy way, with just a few simple steps.

First, we'll walk you through the preparation process, including cleaning your furniture to ensure a smooth surface for painting. Then, we'll show you how to choose the right paint and supplies for your project.

Next, we'll dive into the painting process itself, demonstrating how to apply paint to fabric furniture in a way that ensures a long-lasting finish. You'll learn tips and tricks for avoiding drips and streaks and achieving a professional look.

Finally, we'll share some finishing touches that will take your newly painted fabric furniture to the next level, including how to seal the paint to protect it from wear and tear.

Whether you're a DIY enthusiast or just looking to save some money on furniture upgrades, this tutorial is perfect for you. So grab your paintbrush and let's get started on your next furniture painting project!

description: How to PAINT FABRIC wingback armchairs: no fabric medium, no cracking, and no rub off! If you are wanting to makeover a certain space in your home but can't really afford to buy anything - then, try to paint the fabric upholstery of your old outdated fabric furniture. I used chalk paint and a fabric sealer as an alternative to fabric medium due to fabric medium being out of stock at the craft stores. I actually loved this method, I had no cracking, no rub off! The fabric was smooth and velvety! This is a very cheap DIY to give any piece of fabric furniture a fresh new look!

description:
Come along as I take you shopping at the Goodwill outlet (a.k.a. the Goodwill bins) in search for home decor.

The Goodwill outlet is one of my favorite places to find home decor on a budget. If you are trying to decorate your home and don‚Äôt want to break the bank, I love how far you can stretch your dollar at the Goodwill outlet.

Another thing I love about it is that something from Pottery Barn, Restoration Hardware, or West Elm is not going to cost any more than an item laying right next to it from the dollar store. 

If you‚Äôre new to my channel here welcome! If you are interested in DIY, interior design and decorating, or would like to see more shopping halls, check out my channel, and don‚Äôt forget to hit that subscribe button so you don‚Äôt miss future videos. 

My prayer is that those who watch my content will come away feeling encouraged, inspired, and equipped to create beautiful spaces on a budget. If I can do it, so can you! üòä

description:
I am cleaning this kitchen for free for a family who lost their mom/wife in a tragic accident last year. They have been grieving her death and have had a hard time staying on top of cleaning the house. A neighbor/friend contacted me to let me know of this situation and wondered if I could help. I, of course, was thrilled at the idea of helping out this family. They didn't want a lot of help, but did agree to let me at least clean the kitchen. My heart hurts for their loss. I wish I could do more, but hope having a clean kitchen has at least lifted their spirits somewhat. I'm grateful they let me come in and help because I know it was hard for them to allow someone to do this for them.

description:
The charming French countryside kitchen is a place where time seems to stand still, and memories of generations past come to life. As you step into this rustic sanctuary, you are immediately transported to a bygone era filled with warmth, simplicity, and the aroma of delicious home-cooked meals.
The kitchen's design reflects the traditional French farmhouse style, boasting wooden windows and doors , stone fireplace , and a sturdy oak cabinet that has witnessed countless gatherings of family and friends. The aged brass pots and antique utensils hanging on the walls add to the kitchen's timeless charm, evoking a sense of nostalgia that tugs at the heartstrings.
The heart of this kitchen is the aged hearth, where a crackling fire dances and warms the room during chilly evenings. It is not only a source of heat but also a symbol of comfort and togetherness. Generations of families have gathered around this hearth, sharing stories, laughter, and love while preparing hearty meals.
The kitchen shelves are lined with jars of homemade preserves, pickles, and jams, each containing a tale of seasonal abundance and resourcefulness. Memories of sunny summer afternoons spent picking fresh berries in the nearby fields and preparing the preserves together flood the mind.
A vintage kettle hangs above the stove, a treasured possession passed down through the family. Its patina tells a story of many teas lovingly prepared, and the delicious aromas that have filled the kitchen over the years.
The large farmhouse sink, chipped and weathered, holds memories of countless dishes washed and shared, with hands intertwined as the sun sets on another day in the French countryside. It's a symbol of the simple joys of daily life and the importance of gathering around the table to savor the fruits of labor.
The kitchen table  has witnessed the celebrations of birthdays, anniversaries, and the bittersweet farewells of loved ones. The ancient chandelier tells a story, making it a treasure trove of memories.
The aromas that emanate from the oven are nothing short of tantalizing. Hearty stews, golden-brown bread, and delicate pastries are a testament to the culinary heritage that has been lovingly preserved and passed down through generations. The recipes, often cherished family secrets, are carefully handed down, ensuring that the soul of the French countryside lives on in every bite.
As you sit at the kitchen table, surrounded by the Knick-knacks and dried flowers and herbs, you can't help but be filled with a profound sense of belonging. This kitchen is more than just a room; it's a sanctuary of memories that tie together the past, present, and future. It's a place where generations come together, where stories are shared, and where the heart of the French countryside beats.
In this charming French countryside kitchen, time may continue to pass, but the memories it holds are timeless and eternal. It's a place where the past is honored, the present is celebrated, and the future is embraced with open arms. And as you bid farewell to this picturesque haven, the memories made here will forever linger in your heart, reminding you that the essence of life lies in the simple joys of a shared meal and the love of family and friends.
title: Remember grandma‚Äôs kitchen? The charming French countryside kitchen:where Rustic Meets Elegance

My gardening style has evolved (matured?) ...I started out with a very classic garden style with a huge focus on specific color schemes and more formal design elements...and now I love a more casual, naturalistic, anything goes, low maintenance garden style. description: Here's a full June garden tour of my cottage garden in 2023! My cut flower gardens are working gardens. I cut and sell almost all the flowers at our farm stand. Today I'll take you on a complete garden tour of my English style gardens, secret garden rooms, and raised bed garden. First, we will tour the hydrangea room, then visit the new stone rug, and walk down the main flower walk. Next, we'll check on the raised bed garden that I use for cut flowers, visit the driveway garden, and tour the front garden where I have sunflower steve's van gogh fantasy mix planted. I'm in zone 6b.

description:
Growing your own cut flowers at home can be simple with this ready to go plan of direct seeded and planted flowers--no seed starting needed! We are giving you a ready to go plan for a 4x8 garden bed, complete with information for succession planting for continuous blooms all season. We also go over some tips and tricks for direct seeding success! 

In our plan, the left side of the screen is the North side and therefore where we place the taller sunflowers. Remember you may need to adjust the plan depending on orientation of your garden bed!

You will need:
-one packet sunflower seeds (or more if doing multiple varieties)
-one packet cosmo seeds (or more if doing multiple varieties)
-10 dahlia tubers
-one packet zinnia seeds (or more if doing multiple varieties)
-four garden mums for cutting (we like those from bluestone perennials) or can substitute nasturtium, calendula, marigold.

Cut flower garden layout video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K09HzSiT5T8&t=628s

description:
A well-designed garden creates interest from early spring to late autumn, and beyond if you also select plants for the winter structure. But, for the main growing season, much of this interest comes from flowering and foliage plants. Gardeners who want a low-maintenance landscape should look for perennials that are easy to grow and offer a long flowering period. Most perennials flower for two to four weeks, but longer flowering perennials, such as echinacea and catnip, measure their flowering period in months, not weeks.

Taarak is a happy man when he learns that he can eat whatever he likes for the next eight days after Anjali gives him permission. Watch the fun episode.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Oondha Chashma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in ""Gokuldham Co-operative Society"" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around Jethalal (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Tarak Mehta (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. Jethalal finds a friend and philosopher in Tarak Mehta and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalal's family includes his simpleton wife Daya Ben (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son Tapu (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members residing in the Gokuldham Society. They have often warned Jethalal to reform Tapu or else be prepared to leave the premises. description:
My favorite tropical & exotic flower is...  the Canna Lily!  I love how this flower comes in a variety of heights and colors, both in the flowers as well as the foliage!  Here I go over the Canna Lily care and requirements so you know what to expect if you choose to grow this beautiful specimen!  PLUS, folks up to zone 7 can likely enjoy this full sun flower as a perennial!

My name is Nicole, and My Carolina Garden is in growing zone 8A in Southeastern North Carolina.  Canna Lilies are perennials for me here because my ground doesn't freeze.

I love watching other people's garden tours as much as creating my own!  Sharing gardening ideas and favorite flowers is what this channel is all about, so I hope you enjoy!

For more on gardening in North Carolina, and seeing how my landscape blossoms and expands, stick with me and My Carolina Garden!

description:
Let's talk about ways to save money on your fall decor this year, while we make DIY Fall Centerpieces.  Looking for fall centerpiece ideas?  I'll show you step by step how to make 2 DIY fall centerpieces.  With prices high, you can save money by:
1.  Reusing last year's fall decor in new ways.
2.  Paint pumpkins you already have to give them a new look.
3.  Looking at all of last year's fall decorations and then only buying a few new items to go with last year's items.

I hope you are inspired!  So let's save money on fall decor and make 2 fall table centerpieces.

The first of the sunflowers are blooming, cosmos are starting up, and it won't be long till we have zinnias again too.  The lisianthus is short but beautiful.  The perennial flowers, like phlox, are still saving our butts.  And the oriental lilies are filling the air with their sweet scent.  Join us for a walk through the garden and an update on how things have been growing so far.
__________

Ian and Serina of YOU CANT EAT THE GRASS feel that every small change can make a big difference to the world we live in.  Every garden planted leads to a better future.  We hope to inspire and motivate others to make positive changes in their lives by sharing our journey towards greater sustainability as we build our family farm.  It's hard work to build a life worth living, and completely worth it!

description:
Chow Mein Recipe:
Â¶Ç‰ΩïÂà∂‰ΩúÁÇíÈù¢
Today we are making Chow Mein. Chow Mein means stir fried noodles in English. It‚Äôs a very popular street food that you can find in every neighborhood in China. Almost every Chinese restaurant has Chow Mein on their menus. People love this dish due to its smoky flavor and incredible savory taste. In this video I am going to show you guys my tips for making authentic tasting Chow Mein!

Ingredients:
3oz dry egg noodles
1/2 onion
1.5 oz bean sprouts
2 small size Bok Choy
5 cloves of garlic
1/2 cup of spring onion
1 egg
1 tsp light soy sauce
1/2 tsp dark soy sauce 
1 tsp oyster sauce 
1 tbsp cooking wine
2 tbsp cooking oil

Directions:
Let‚Äôs start with preparing the veggies. First, we are going to cut half of onion into thin slices. Get 2 Bok choy and cut the roots off. Separate the leaves from the stalks and cut them into shreds. Take one 1 spring onion. Also Separate the green part from the white part and cut them into shred. Slice about 4-5 garlic cloves into thin pieces. Crack one egg and mix well. 

Turn on the stove and add some hot water, 1/4 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp cooking oil into the pot. Once water starts to boil, put about 3 OZ noodles in and let it cook for about 2-3 mins. I am using Chinese style dry egg noodles here.  If you don‚Äôt have that, you can also use spaghetti noodles. once the noodles are cooked, we will need drain them and put them into the cold water, soak for 1-2 mins to stop the cooking process. Drain the noodles again and spread them out on a tray. Once the noodles are dry, add 1 tsp of cooling oil, mix well. This way noodles will stay crunchy and won‚Äôt stick together when we cook them. 

Next, we are going to make the sauce. Put the garlic slices into a bowl and add 1 tsp of light soy sauce, 1/2 tsp of dark soy sauce, 1 tsp of oyster sauce, 1 tbs of cooking wine and 1/4 tsp of salt. Mix well.

Preheat the wok with median high heat until we can see the smoke. Add 1 tbs of cooking oil and eggs. Stir fry and break the egg into small pieces. Remove the eggs. Lower the heat to median and put the noodles in. let it cook for about 1-2 mins. Flip to the other side and cook for another 1-2 mins. once both sides are crispy, remove them and set aside. Add 1 tbs of cooking oil and cook the sprouts and onions with median high heat for about 1 min and keep adding the shredded Bok Choy stalks and white part of the green onions. Stir fry for about 30 seconds. And then bring the noodles back, pour our sauce in, mix well.  Keeping adding the Bok Choy leaves and green part of the spring onion. Stir fry for about 30 seconds. Finally add the eggs and mix everything together.

description:
How to Make Chinese Homemade Shrimp Fried Rice 

Recipe Ingredients :

Shrimp Marinade:

10-20 pieces of cleaned shrimps
1/4 tsp of salt
1/4 tsp pf white pepper or black pepper
1/2 tsp of cooking wine 
1/2 tsp of corn starch
1/4 tsp of sesame oil 

Fried rice:

1 cup of rice
4 and 1/4 tsp of cooking oil
2 eggs
1 cup of carrots and peas
1/2 cup of onion 
1/4 cup of green onion
1/2 tsp of salt 
1/2 tsp of sugar 

Notes:
1: Soak the rice at least 30 mins before cook the rice
2: Add little bit salt and oil to the water before boil the carrots and peas
3: Don't overcook the shrimp
4: Preheat the wok or pan before adding the rice

Directions:

Take 1 cup of the rice and wash the rice several times. Make sure to use fresh water each time until we see the clear water comes out. This step is very important. it will make the cooked rice less sticky. Soak the rice for 30 mins. Drain the rice. Add the washed rice, 1 cup of water into a rice cooker. I have always heard that fried rice is best made with day-old rice, but from my cooking experience‚Ä¶ fresh-cooked rice works too. we just need to spread the rice out on a tray and let them cool for about 20-30 mins. 

Crack 2 eggs and separate yolk from whites. Whisk the egg whites and mix the egg yolk with the rice. Marinate the shrimps by adding 1/4 tsp of salt, 1/4 tsp of white pepper or black pepper, 1/2 tsp of cooking wine, 1/2 corn starch and 1/4 Next, we are going to dice the carrot, onion. Chop the green onion. 

After preparing all the ingredients. Turn on the stove add some water and turn the heat on high. Once the water starts to boil, add carrots and peas. let it cook for about 2 mins. Tun the stove off and take the carrot and peas out. 

Get a fry pan. Turn the heat to median low. Add 1 tsp of oil and add the egg white. Stir fry until it‚Äôs cooked. When egg whites are cooked, remove from the pan and set aside. Add 1 tsp of oil and cook the shrimps with median high heat. Cook about 20-25 seconds for each side. Don‚Äôt overcook the shrimps, otherwise they will become hard and chewy. 

I use a traditional Chinese wok to make the fried rice since this kind wok can handle the high cooking temperature. If you don‚Äôt have a wok, you can use non-stick fry pan as well. Turn the heat to the highest. Once you see the smoke are coming from the wok. We are ready to add the oil. Add about 2 tsp of cooking oil and then add the rice. lower the heat to median low. don‚Äôt stir it immediately. let it cook for about 20 seconds. And then we are going to stir fry for about 2 mins and season it with 1/2 tsp of salt and 1/2 tsp of sugar. Turn the heat to medium high and add onion first. Once you can smell the aroma, add the cooked egg white, shrimp, carrots, and peas. Stir fry about 1 min until rice is separate. Add green onion; Turn the heat to max high and stir fry about 30 seconds. Give it a taste and we are DONE!!!

smoked paprika

Directions:
Begin by removing the core of the cabbage and slicing it into your desired thickness. Dice your onion and chop the bacon as well. Over medium heat, fry the bacon until crispy and remove with a slotted spoon. In the same pan, add your onions and cook for 3-4 minutes or until they start to get tender. Next, add your garlic and cook for 1-2 minutes. Add your cabbage and mix to combine. Season to taste with listed seasonings and add in your worcestershire, sugar, and vinegar. Add butter and cover the pan with a lid and cook for 10 minutes on low. Cook, covered, checking occasionally, until cabbage is tender. Taste as you go and adjust the seasoning as needed. Add your bacon once the cabbage is tender and mix to combine. You can add sausage to this as well.

description:
It's so delicious that I make this almost every weekend! A simple broccoli recipe

Ingredients and recipe:
250g broccoli 
Hot water 
Soak for 5 minutes
Drain the water after 5 minutes
Chop the broccoli into small pieces
Add to a bowl
3 eggs
Salt 
Black pepper 
Whisk the eggs with a fork 
Pour on the broccoli 
20g green onion
Chop
Add to the broccoli 
Dice 1/2 onion
20g mozzarella cheese (optional) 
Salt & black pepper
Mix well 
Medium heat 
olive oil 
Pour into the frying pan
Spread evenly
Fry for 3-5 minutes
Flip over with a plate
Fry for another 2 minutes
Add some olive oil
Done!

description:
UPDATE:  I made a new bread pudding video, that you can see here:  https://youtu.be/yAgl9cxU-Z0
Hey, y'all!  I'm Jan, and welcome to my attempt to video my cooking, baking, and gardening. I'm learning, so please bear with me.  The meals/baking, etc., I've been doing for decades. Recording it on anything, never. Lol  
This started as a virtual recipe book for my kids when I'm gone. Then I decided to start recording my garden as sort of a diary, especially the woes of deep south heat and humidity, and trying to keep my plants alive during summer so that they can produce until (hopefully)November. 
I don't claim to be a chef or master gardener. I'm an idiot, and probably screw up more things than I get right. 
But, I absolutely love cooking and gardening. I'll grow/cook/bake pretty much anything, once. Or, try to.
Hope you'll stick around for this journey with me!  Also, if you have any cooking requests, just yell. 

Now to the recipe: 
Bread Pudding - it's easy to make, and delicious! You can make this many different ways. But, any way you make it, you'll love it.  

You'll need: 9x13 bake dish, buttered (or two 8x8s or one deep 8x8) 
16 pieces of sandwich bread - cut into cubes or torn into one inch chunks. You can use any bread here - sandwich, brioche, biscuits, hotdog buns, etc.) Just make sure it's about equal to a loaf of bread. 
1 and 1/2 cups of Milk (or hot water) 
1- 14oz can Sweetened Condensed Milk 
3 Large eggs, beaten  
1/3 cup packed brown sugar (or granulated sugar) 
1/2 Stick of Salted butter, melted *Note- If you use unsalted butter, add a pinch of salt to the mixture. 
1 cup Raisins *Optional (you can use any thing you want.. raisins, currents, pecans, walnuts, or nothing at all
1 Tbs Vanilla (plus 1 teaspoon for the vanilla sauce)  
1 Teaspoon of Cinnamon 
1/2 cup powdered sugar (vanilla sauce) 
1 tbs milk (vanilla sauce)

In a large bowl, whisk together your milk, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, butter, sugar, cinnamon. 
In your greased bake dish, pour your bread cubes in and raisins (if using). 
Then pour your milk/egg/sugar batter over your bread 
Take a spoon on your hand and press the bread down into the liquid to make sure all bread is absorbing some milk mixture.  
Let sit 30 minutes or even over night. 

Oven at 350F (180C) 
Bake 30-40 minutes.  

*Optional Vanilla Sauce 
1/2 cup powdered sugar 
1 teaspoon vanilla 
1 tbs milk  
Mix well, and drizzle over your bread pudding once it comes out of the oven.  
-- You can also top it with ice cream, cool whip, syrup. Anything you like.

Enjoy!
 
**You can freeze this if you want to bake it ahead. Place in fridge 24 hours before needed, to thaw it. 

My email is maddamsel@gmail.com     
Twitter is: https://twitter.com/Souther83578888

description:
Today I'm going to show you how I make the BEST 2 INGREDIENT BISCUIT YOU'LL EVER EAT. Grab your ingredients and cook along with me. RECIPE BELOW

‚ñ∂Ô∏é SHOP MY FAVORITE PRODUCTS: https://www.amazon.com/shop/howdoyoucook-backtobasics

Ingredients you'll need:
‚Ä¢  2 - Cups Self Rising Flour (Any brand - I used White Lily)
‚Ä¢ 1 1/2 - Cups Heavy Whipping Cream
‚Ä¢ Shortening for your Biscuit Pan/Dish
‚Ä¢ Wax Paper (Optional)
‚Ä¢ Extra Flour for your Biscuit Cutting Surface 

Instructions:
‚Ä¢ Preheat oven to 450 degrees
‚Ä¢ Add shortening to your baking pan - Making sure to cover bottom and sides (USE PLENTY) Set dish aside
‚Ä¢ Sift your 2 cups of flour into your mixing bowl (DO NOT PACK YOUR FLOUR WHEN MEASURING)
‚Ä¢ Add your heavy whipping cream
‚Ä¢ Mix flour and whipping cream until flour is moistened (You can use a mixing spoon or your hands)
‚Ä¢ Place wax paper on a table or counter
‚Ä¢ Add some flour to wax paper so flour doesn't stick to wax paper
‚Ä¢ Knead and fold your dough until you are ready to begin cutting out your biscuits (DO NOT OVER WORK YOUR DOUGH) (DOUGH WILL BE STICKY - THIS IS OKAY!)
‚Ä¢ Roll or pat out your biscuit dough to your desired cutting thickness
‚Ä¢ Use a cup or biscuit cutter to cut out your biscuits
‚Ä¢ Place cut out biscuits in/on your baking pan so they are touching each other (This helps them to rise, instead of spreading out and becoming flat)
‚Ä¢ Bake at 450 degrees until top is golden brown & cooked thoroughly (Approximately 15-20 minutes) OVENS VARY 
‚Ä¢ Serve immediately or until you're ready to eat

Frying Pan Bread (No Egg, No Oven, No Knead) Easiest Pan bread (No need to touch the dough) 

All-purpose flour 2 1/4 cups  (280 g) 
Yeast 1 tsp
Salt 1 tsp
Sugar 1 tsp
Lukewarm water 1 cup (250 ml) 
Olive oil 1 tbsp

1) Mix the dry ingredients: flour, yeast, sugar, salt
2) Add water and mix
3) Cover and let the dough rise for an hour
4) Grease the pan with olive oil
5) Degas dough by rolling the dough with a spatula
6) Sprinkle with flour and roll a few more times
7) Put the dough in the pan
8) Cover and let the dough rise for 30 minutes
9) Cover and cook over low heat (20-25 min)
10) Turn over and cook for another 5 minutes without the lid

description:
Welcome back to Cook and PhotoShoot.

Today, we have an exciting recipe to take your bread-making skills to the next level. 
We will make delicious homemade ciabatta rolls using a simple no-knead method, just the stretch and fold method.  
These rolls are light, airy, and packed with flavour. The best part? You won't believe how easy they are to make! So, let's dive right in and get started!


Easy Homemade Ciabatta Rolls - No-Knead Recipe
Ingredients:
400g warm water
Two teaspoons honey
500g white bread flour
21g fast-action yeast
7g salt
Olive oil 

Instructions:
Combine the white bread flour, salt, and fast-action yeast in a large mixing bowl.

In a separate bowl, mix the warm water with honey until the honey is dissolved.

Pour the honey water mixture into the bowl with the dry ingredients while stirring. Continue stirring until a sticky dough forms.

Transfer the sticky dough to a large, well-oiled (use olive oil) bowl to prevent sticking. Cover the bowl with a clean kitchen towel and rest for 20 minutes.

Before stretching the dough, wet your hands with olive oil or water to prevent sticking.

After 20 minutes, gently stretch and fold the dough. Try to be very gentle and keep the dough airy.

Cover the bowl again and let it rest for another 20 minutes. 

Repeat this stretching and folding process four times, with 20 minutes of rest between each round.

Before the last two stretches, preheat the oven to 180-200¬∞C (350-390¬∞F). Place a metal container inside the oven as well.


Once the dough has gone through the final two stretches and folds, it's time to shape the rolls. Dust your work surface with flour and flip the bowl upside down to release the dough onto the surface. 

Use a knife or dough cutter to gently cut the dough into desired sizes and shape the rolls.
Transfer the shaped rolls onto a baking tray lined with greaseproof paper.

Place the tray in the oven and add hot water to the preheated metal container; it generates steam.
Bake the ciabatta rolls for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown.

Once baked, remove the rolls from the oven and let them cool on a wire rack.

Your homemade ciabatta rolls are now ready to be enjoyed! They are perfect for sandwiches, sliders, or served alongside soups and salads.
 
 
Thank you for watching, and enjoy your Ciabatta rolls.
Please leave comments and suggestions for the next video.

description:
Multigrain bread 
It is a bread with two or more types of grain packed with lots of nutrients and other goodies. 
Ingredients: 
250g Strong Flour 
30g White Rye Flour 
30g Buckwheat Flour 
80g Spelt Wholemeal Flour 
300g Water 
7g Yeast 
9g Honey 
15g Salt 
Mix the seeds as you like; I use 
Two tablespoons of fried onion (essential it gives a pleasant smell) 
One tablespoon of pumpkin seeds.
One tablespoon of sesame seeds.
One tablespoon of sunflower seeds. 
Mix the following ingredients: 
Water, salt, yeast, honey. 
One by one, add all measured flour. 
For this bread, I used a kitchen mixer. You can knead bread by hand or use other techniques like stretch and fold. 
https://youtu.be/MQ9wXDMQngU
In the beginning, the dough is very wet and sticky. Keep kneading until it starts pulling off from the mixing bowl. You can add more bread flour if the dough is too wet. 
When your dough is ready, add mixed seeds and don't forget about fried onion, then give a little stir. 
Cover until it's doubled in size. 
Preheat the oven to 200C and place a metal pan or tray to create steam. 
Dust very well surface with flour and remove dough from the bowl. 
Make a rectangle shape, fold and roll before putting it into a proofing basket or baking tray. 
Let it proof until it has doubled the size. 
Baking When the dough rises well, gently place it on a tray and score. 
Then bake for 30-35min at 200c. 
Before closing the door, adds hot water to preheat the tray to create steam. 
Before cutting the first slice, cool down the bread for at least 30 minutes.

description:
You know I love cold fermentation. Usually, I stick with cold bulk fermentation and then finish the final proof at room temperature the next day. Cold proofing flips the process upside down. The bulk fermentation is done at room temperature and the final proof is finished in the fridge. Cold proofing is the perfect method for breakfast bakes because all you need to do the next day is pre-heat the oven and bake the bread. You can find a few recipes using this method in the Cold Fermented Dough playlist. 

Little ciabatta rolls are ideal for breakfast. They are hearty, taste great, and can hold a lot of topping/fillings. You can leave them as they are, or you can toast them. What makes this recipe even better is that there is no kneading. The dough is simply folded a few times during bulk fermentation instead.

description:
Homemade Wholemeal Spelt Bread

This recipe makes delicious and nutritious wholemeal spelt bread with a lovely nutty flavour and chewy texture.

Ingredients:
500g organic wholemeal spelt flour
10g salt
11g fast action yeast
350g warm water
2 tbsp pumpkin seeds (optional)
2 tbsp pine nuts (optional)

Instructions:
‚Ä¢ Combine the dry ingredients (flour, salt, yeast) in a large mixing bowl. Mix well to distribute evenly.
‚Ä¢ Add the warm water and mix to form a shaggy dough.
‚Ä¢ Let the dough rest for 20 minutes to allow the flour to hydrate and the gluten to develop.
‚Ä¢ Wet your hands to prevent sticking. Fold the dough over itself five times to strengthen the gluten network.
‚Ä¢ Place the dough in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled in size.
‚Ä¢ Punch down the dough to release air bubbles. Wet your hands or use olive oil before folding the optional pumpkin seeds and pine nuts for added flavour and texture.
‚Ä¢ Divide dough into two portions for smaller loaves, or shape into one large round loaf to bake in a bread tin. Let rise until doubled in size again.
‚Ä¢ Preheat oven to 200¬∞C. Place a small oven-proof dish with hot water on the bottom rack to create steam.
‚Ä¢ Bake smaller loaves for 30 minutes directly on a baking sheet. Or bake a large loaf for 35-40 minutes in a greased tin.

‚Ä¢ Cool before slicing, and enjoy the hearty homemade spelt bread!

Here is some quick information about the benefits of using wholemeal spelt flour:
‚Ä¢ Higher protein content than regular wheat flour - Spelt contains more protein which provides sustained energy.
‚Ä¢ More nutrients - Milling the whole spelt grain preserves all the nutritional bran and germ, making it richer in B vitamins, minerals like iron and magnesium, and fibre.
‚Ä¢ Easier to digest - The gluten in spelt flour is more soluble, making it easier to break down for people with sensitivities.
‚Ä¢ Nutty, sweet flavour - Spelt has a delicious nutty taste and sweetness that comes through in baked goods.
‚Ä¢ Doesn't require strong gluten development - The gluten strands in spelt are more fragile, so it doesn't need intensive kneading.
‚Ä¢ Denser texture - The lower gluten content gives spelt bread a pleasant dense, and chewy texture.

So, in summary, wholemeal spelt flour makes wonderfully tasty and nutritious bread packed with protein, fibre and important nutrients! Let me know if you need any other spelt flour facts.

Thanks for learning how to make a tasty artisan-style wholemeal spelt loaf with me today. 
Stay connected by subscribing, and I'll keep the recipes coming!

description:
#roastpotatoes #airfryerrecipes #airfryercooking 
Roast spuds are the best part of any roast dinner. You know how it is - you have to cook extra because everyone around the table has room for more!

If there's one thing I've learned, is that you can't beat cooking them in the traditional way. The question is, how can we get the taste of a traditionally cooked roast potato, with the speed and convenience of using the air fryer? Ta-da! The answer lies in this video.

The air fryer offers health benefits and allows us to cook food using the minimum amount of oil. The crisper plate helps the hot air to circulate around the food and food is crisp and cooked much quicker ...BUT, using the crisper plate with just a spray of oil can result in quite dry roast potatoes.

I've experimented and tried this different ways and cooking them in a more traditional way on the base of the air fryer in a few tablespoons of oil, results in a far superior roastie ...and they'll be cooked in a fraction of the time it takes in a conventional oven.

Follow my tip for that crispy exterior and use a good quality floury potato for that soft, fluffy interior.

As usual, hit the like button, subscribe for more, share it with your friends and let me know how you get on!

Wow! This is one of my best air fryer recipes. These Yorkshire puddings were stellar! I've perfected this recipe after much trial and error ...and I believe I've produced Yorkshire puddings that are FAR better than anything I've ever made in the oven.

This method resulted in huge, inflated, pillows of crispiness, with just the right amount of breadiness inside for mopping up your gravy.

I think the secret is not to have too much flour, a reasonable amount of milk and to use decent sized shallow tins. The usual rules apply: the oil needs to be smoking hot before you pour the batter in, you need to work quickly, and once the drawer is closed, don't open it again until they're cooked.

They literally take 16 minutes to cook - that's half the cooking time they'd have in the oven, not to mention how long it would take your regular oven to preheat to such a high temperature!

These truly are AMAZING! Give them a go and let me know how they turned out for you.

DIY Chalk Paint Recipe:
2 parts acrylic or latex paint
1 part pure talc (Do not use cornstarch baby powder it won't work because the cornstarch is too slippery!) Here are a couple of links to talc products:
https://www.amazon.com/Lab-Grade-Talc-Powder-Mesh-500g/dp/B0787MM9DH/ref=sr_1_3?dchild=1&keywords=talc&qid=1620824376&sr=8-3
https://www.amazon.com/Nivea-Pure-Talc-400Gm/dp/B00FQH5H6O/ref=sr_1_8?dchild=1&keywords=talc&qid=1620824406&sr=8-8

Mix very well, shaking is best. Check the paint often to make sure that the all the talc is incorporated. Use on any dull surface such as raw wood, plastic, metal. If you are gluing the project onto something, glue it first, then paint it. Sometimes the baby powder doesn't hold the glue very well.
Let me know if you need help!!

description:
Popular pineapple dessert that is quick and easy to make with only 3 ingredients! 

Ingredients 
- crushed pineapple 
- sweetened condensed milk 
- cool whip 

Steps: 
1. Drain all the juice from the crushed pineapple 
2. Put the pineapple into a pan and mix in 1/3 of the condensed milk tin (this is based on taste, for sweeter results add more and for less sweet add less - taste as you go) 
3. Add in about half the tub of cool whip and mix it into the pineapple until everything is covered ( add more as needed) 
4. Optional: Decorate the top with whip cream, nuts or fruit
5. Put in fridge or freezer to cool and serve!
title: 3 Ingredient Quick Pineapple Dessert (Ready In Less Than 5 Minutes!!)

description:
Get the recipe here: https://www.dimitrasdishes.com/mediterranean-chickpea-salad/

Ingredients
2 (15-oz/439g) cans chickpeas, rinsed and drained
1 English cucumber, peeled and diced
2 roasted red peppers, diced
5-6 scallions, thinly sliced
1-2 cups grape tomatoes, halved
4 oz (115g) feta cheese
1/2-1 cup Kalamata olives, pitted and chopped
a handful of fresh parsley, finely chopped
2-3 tablespoons finely chopped fresh mint leaves
2-3 peperoncini peppers, sliced (optional)
The Dressing:

1/4 cup olive oil
2 tablespoons vinegar
2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice
1 garlic clove, grated
1 teaspoon dried crushed oregano
salt, to taste
freshly cracked black pepper, to taste
Instructions
Make the Dressing: Combine all of the dressing ingredients, except the salt and pepper, in a bowl and whisk them together.

Combine all of the salad ingredients in a large bowl and season with salt and pepper. Crumble the feta cheese on top and pour the dressing over the salad. Toss together and serve immediately or chilled.

Notes
Leftovers can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 2-3 days.

description:
Star by sanitizing your ball jars and lids and set aside.

Chop fresh dill about 1/4 cup or use the heads. Gather your red pepper flakes, your vinegar, your water and your sugar. 

Next you're going to add one cup of water and one cup of apple cider vinegar to your pot, bring it to a soft boil add 2 tablespoons of sugar I like to use all natural And add 1 tablespoon of salt, kosher or pink Himalayan. I definitely don't recommend iodized salt. Turn off heat and set your brain aside to drop in temp ( your brine can be warm but not hot)

Slice up your cucumbers and add 1 tsp of dill to the jar 1 tsp red pepper flakes and 1 tsp to 2 tsp of minced or chopped garlic. Place cucumber into a jar do not pack but definitely put them in somewhat tight so that the liquid can form around the pickle. Pour the brine just to the first lip of jar put the top on and give it a good shake and then I loosen the lid until they cool completely, or I should say are at room temperature before sealing them and placing them in refrigerator. In 24 hours they are ready to enjoy!Ôøº

description:
King Charles evicts disgraced Prince Andrew from Buckingham Palace. King Charles has sensationally sent his disgraced brother Prince Andrew packing, according to reports.

The scandal-scarred royal, who was famously stripped of his royal and military honors by his late mother, Queen Elizabeth II, has been told to find a new place to live immediately, the Sun reports.
‚ÄúThe king has made it clear that Buckingham Palace is no place for Prince Andrew,‚Äù a source told the outlet of the decision, which comes just months before King Charles III‚Äôs coronation, set for May 6.
Andrew, who has had his back against the wall since his alleged friendship with disgraced financier Jeffrey Epstein came to light, has been told ‚Äúthere is no longer any place‚Äù for him at Buckingham Palace, the official royal residence. First his office closed last year and now his sleeping quarters,‚Äù the insider told the Sun. ‚ÄúAndrew loved having a suite at Buckingham Palace, where he was not only set up for marital life with Sarah Ferguson but used it as a bachelor‚Äôs pad after his divorce.‚Äù 
‚ÄúHe brought back a string of new girlfriends to his home in the palace ‚Äî even model Caprice. A bachelor‚Äôs flat in St James‚Äô Palace doesn‚Äôt have the same allure for a single man,‚Äù the source added. 

A 10-year-long renovation, costing upward of $400 million, is reportedly due to take place at the palace, which includes Andrew‚Äôs suite, known as the Chamber Floor. If Andrew wishes to stay in London, King Charles has reportedly told him that his only other option is his other royal residence, St. James. Andrew also shares a 31-room Royal Lodge mansion in Windsor with his ex-wife, Sarah Ferguson. The eviction serves as a fresh blow to Andrew, who was kicked out of his Buckingham Palace office last year.

‚ÄúAny presence at the palace is officially over,‚Äù a source told the outlet in December. ‚ÄúThe king has made it clear. He isn‚Äôt a working royal. He‚Äôs on his own.‚Äù Andrew, who was barred from using his HRH (‚ÄúHis Royal Highness‚Äù) moniker following his association with pedophile Epstein, also lost his patronages last year. While he is still a Royal Knight of the Garter and a Knight Grand Cross of the Royal Victorian Order, he was told face to face by his mother that he would no longer be known as His Royal Highness.

The monarch, who was 94 when she died in September, broke the news to the father of two at Windsor Castle in January last year. That same month, she also took away his military titles. With the Queen‚Äôs approval and agreement, the Duke of York‚Äôs military affiliations and royal patronages have been returned to the Queen,‚Äù Buckingham Palace said in a statement at the time. The retraction of Andrew‚Äôs official royal labels came amid his sexual assault case filed by Virginia Giuffre, who has long claimed that Epstein made her have ‚Äúdisgusting‚Äù sex with the royal three times, starting in 2001 when she was just 17.

description:
In this captivating video, we delve into the lesser-known aspects of Hollywood legend John Wayne's personal life. While the Duke was an iconic figure on the silver screen, his off-screen life was just as intriguing. Today, we explore the lives of John Wayne's children and uncover the untold stories that shaped their destinies.

John Wayne, the epitome of the American cowboy, was a larger-than-life character both on and off the screen. However, behind the fame and fortune, he was a devoted family man with four children. Join us as we take a journey through their lives, successes, struggles, and the impact of being raised by one of Hollywood's most enduring stars.

Michael Wayne: The eldest son of John Wayne, Michael followed in his father's footsteps and established himself as a successful producer. We'll uncover the challenges he faced as he carved his own path in the film industry and the legacy he left behind.

Patrick Wayne: Often seen alongside his father in several movies, Patrick Wayne became a recognizable face in Hollywood. But what happened to him after his acting days? Discover how he transitioned to a different role behind the scenes and how his father's influence shaped his choices.

Melinda Wayne Munoz: The only daughter of John Wayne, Melinda lived a life somewhat away from the spotlight. We'll explore her journey as she sought a private life and her contributions to philanthropy, honoring her father's legacy in her own unique way.

Ethan Wayne: The youngest of John Wayne's children, Ethan had the daunting task of living up to the legendary name. Find out how he managed to strike a balance between his father's legacy and personal aspirations, and how he keeps the Duke's memory alive today.

Toni Wayne LaCava, John Wayne's adopted daughter, chose a path away from the glitz and glamour of Hollywood. Her life took a different turn as she pursued a career outside the entertainment industry, far from the spotlight her father thrived in. Discover the inspiring story of Toni's resilience and the impact of growing up in the shadow of one of the world's most famous actors.
Aissa Wayne: The Trials and Triumphs of the Youngest Wayne
The youngest of John Wayne's children, Aissa Wayne, faced a life filled with both heartbreak and triumph. We explore the challenges she encountered as she fought to uphold her father's name amidst legal battles and personal struggles, while also finding her own path in the world.

In this video, we aim to shed light on the often overlooked aspects of John Wayne's family life, showcasing how the Duke's influence extended beyond the silver screen and into the hearts of his beloved children. Join us on this insightful journey into the lives of John Wayne's children, their achievements, and how they continue to carry their father's legacy forward.

If you're a fan of classic Hollywood history or simply curious about the human side of the Duke, don't miss this must-watch video that uncovers What Happened To John Wayne's Children. Remember to like, subscribe, and hit the notification bell to never miss an upload as we bring you more captivating stories from the world of entertainment.

Alan Arkin, passed away on June 29th, at the age of aged 89. He was an American actor, best known for his role, as Edwin Hoover, in the 2006 film, Little Miss Sunshine, for which he won an Oscar, for Best Supporting Actor. 
Nicolas Coster, passed away on June 26th, 2023, at the age of 89. He was best known for his role, as Lionel Lockridge, in the American television soap opera, Santa Barbara.
Glenda Jackson passed away on June 15th, 2023, at the age of 87. She was one of the world's greatest actresses, and a politician. She has played roles in dozens of popular films, and TV series, and received many prestigious awards, including two Oscars for Best Actress. She won her first Academy Award, for her role, in the 1969 film, Women in Love. In 1974, she received her second Oscar, for her role in the romantic comedy, A Touch of Class.
Julian Sands, died at the age of 65. On 13th January 2023, Sands went missing while hiking in the San Gabriel Mountains. On 24 June 2023, his body was discovered. He was known for his roles in the films, A Room with a View, The Medallion, Warlock, and The Killing Fields.

description:
BACKSTORY: 
Incredible drone video(taken from my drone) from the landslide that is occurring in 8 Peartree Lane in Rolling Hills Estates shows just how much damage the landslide has caused to the houses there, even splitting rooms in half. In one of the videos, a kids basketball rim can be seen in a backyard, with the backyard being nearly cut in half right in front of the basketball rim where kids play. In another video, it can be seen that a bedroom & living room are split in half right where the beds and couches are. It can even be seen that some houses have the top of their roof being on the same level as the sidewalk that was used to walk into their houses. What‚Äôs most noticeable from all the footage is a big split/line in the land that shows the land sliding into the canyon, almost looking like a scene seen in the famous movie ‚Äú2012‚Äù.

It‚Äôs important to note that from the last post that I covered about this, it was only 12 houses that were evacuated due to this natural disaster, however, now less than a dozen or so more houses have been evacuated, and another 17 more homes are being monitored by the LA County Fire Department (LACoFD). This comes as the LACoFD determines that this landslide is bigger than what they had originally thought, and now more homes are in danger. LACoFD had stated all they could do at this point is let nature do its thing and wait until all the houses fall into the canyon, as it is too dangerous and risky to go in as the land is still sliding. The land has so far shifted 20 feet since it started, and it continues to grow. Professionals who cover Geological Sciences state that the landslide is most likely not 100% due to the steepness of the hill or the rocks below - as the land is moving way too fast for that to be the main cause -  but rather it is water that can cause this land to move fast. Speculations state that this year's heavy rains were what could be a major factor that could have caused water to play a main role in the landslide. This landslide will go down in history for being one of the most unprecedented & major landslides in the South Bay, and even in California. 

To make matters even worse, criminals have taken advantage of the evacuated houses, and on 7/13 some had broken into the evacuated houses and taken items& belongings of those who lived there. Luckily the LA County Sheriff's Department(lomita station), and with the help of the Torrance Police Department, were able to catch the suspects and arrest them in a difficult search. Bravo!

Denzel Washington

Washington's career as a film actor took off in the 1990s, with memorable performances in movies like "Malcolm X," "Glory," and "Philadelphia." He has also starred in many other successful movies, including "Training Day," "The Hurricane," and "Remember the Titans."

In this real human trafficking story, we are share Belle's remarkable journey and the powerful reunion between Belle and her family. Subscribe: https://bit.ly/2RhELf3

Belle was born in Romania to a lower-income family. Because of the poverty in the area, child human trafficking is not uncommon. In Belle‚Äôs situation, the doctors in her hospital stole her from her family to a human trafficking orphanage where she was adopted by a family for a large sum. Her story is one of incredible persistence of trying to find her family. When we heard about her story at Operation Underground Railroad, we stepped in to help her reunite and meet her family for the first time. You will be in awe with her story and you won‚Äôt want to miss this amazingly beautiful reunion.

description:
How To Catch A Pimp: With an estimated 100,000 children involved in prostitution in the Philippines, one Australian father has gone undercover, posing as a sex tourist to uncover a criminal underworld of pimps and victims. 

Subscribe to Journeyman here: http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=journeymanpictures

As a devout Christian with tee-total parents, getting into character as a paedophile was always going to be a stretch for Tony Kirwan. "I was extremely uncomfortable when I first started doing this", says Kirwan. Yet his distress at the world of sleaze and exploitation emboldened him to pose as its worst type of customer. After becoming aware of the scale of child trafficking in Thailand, he founded Destiny Rescue, a charity funded by donations and mostly staffed by volunteers. "I've got no specific skills in this other than I guess a heart of a dad", he says. Now he is part of a motley crew with no background in law enforcement, whose assistance to under-resourced local police is essential. "At any time we'd have a couple of dozen agents around the world in six different countries, ready to go out into the brothels... and get some people arrested and more children rescued", says Kirwan. He claims to have seen 2,500 children and young adults rescued from trafficking in the last seven years, with an 80% success rate in not returning. We watch as months of preparation come to a head, culminating in the biggest raid in Destiny Rescue's history.

Psalm 91, often referred to as the "Psalm of Protection," is a sacred passage in the Bible that offers profound comfort, solace, and assurance of God's divine presence and safeguarding. It is a timeless prayer that has touched the hearts of countless individuals throughout history.

In this powerful Psalm, we find words of hope and trust in God's unwavering care and protection. It speaks of finding refuge in the shadow of the Almighty, dwelling in the shelter of His wings, and experiencing His faithfulness as a shield and fortress. It reminds us that when we trust in God, we can face life's challenges with courage and confidence, knowing that He is our refuge and stronghold.

Join us on a spiritual journey as we delve into the rich and transformative verses of Psalm 91. Discover the profound peace that comes from entrusting your life into the hands of the Most High. Be uplifted by the promises of God's deliverance, His angels' watchful presence, and His steadfast love that shields and sustains us in times of trouble.

As we explore this psalm together, we invite you to reflect on its timeless wisdom and apply its principles to your own life. Experience the transformative power of dwelling in God's presence and finding security in His unfailing love. Allow the words of Psalm 91 to renew your faith, strengthen your spirit, and instill a sense of peace that transcends all understanding.

Subscribe to our channel and embark on this journey of spiritual exploration through Psalm 91. Let the words of this sacred prayer inspire and guide you, providing solace, protection, and divine assurance in every season of life. Ten years ago, Jessa Crisp escaped her last trafficker. If there is one thing that her life says is the reality that although healing is a life long process, it is possible. 2017 will forever be the year that Jessa shared her story on camera for the first time, on our platform, in greater detail, giving hope to SO many men and women from all around the world. Sharing her story might have been one of the most challenging experiences of her life.

Many have complained about low sound issues in the original video and so we have decided to fix it and now it's much better. In this movie--for those who haven't watched--Jessa has bravely recounted how she overcame a childhood of being gang raped, sexually abused by family members and trafficked. Her abuse started aged 10 in her home country of Canada where she was molested by members of her own family. As a child, she was made to pose for pornographers, had to perform degrading sex acts and was raped in front of the cameras.

Some people might be recognizing Jessa because of her story. Jessa does not want to be defined by her past, she wants to share her story, however, she doesn't want to be known for it. For us, Jessa Crisp is a victor and and a role model: she shows what it means to be a strong, resilient human being. She keeps chasing her dreams, and never gives up. We are proud to announce that Jessa is now officially graduated with her M.A. in Clinical Mental Health Counseling. BRAVO.

This story needs to go viral. If you agree please share and help us and Jessa raise awareness.
