description:
In this video, we will talk about 8 Things That Emotionally Hurt Your German Shepherd.

‚úÖ‚úÖ Develop your dog's hidden intelligence to eliminate bad behavior and get a smarter dog.
‚ûú ‚ûú https://tinyurl.com/thecagdotyt ‚úÖ‚úÖ
___________________________________________
To Be Clear: German Shepherds are intelligent, sociable, and energetic dogs that need a lot of affection, stimulation, and care to remain healthy and happy. These dogs' emotional well-being and behavior can suffer as a result of specific events and circumstances, though. In this video, we'll look at 8 things that might emotionally hurt German Shepherds. In order to provide these dogs the care they require to thrive, it is essential to understand what can emotionally hurt them. Let‚Äôs Get Started.




Number 1: Sudden disappearance of a trusted person or companion animal.
German Shepherds may experience emotional trauma when a dependable person or pet suddenly disappears. These dogs are extremely social animals that develop close relationships with their human families and other animals. German Shepherds may suffer a sense of sorrow, perplexity, and abandonment when a beloved family member or pet abruptly departs from their lives. Depression, separation anxiety, and other behavioral problems may emerge from this.
Number 2: Change of routine or environment.
For German Shepherds, a change in routine or environment might be upsetting. Because these dogs thrive on predictability and consistency, abrupt changes may make them feel uneasy and confused. Negative behaviors like barking, chewing, or even hostility may result from this. German Shepherds can adjust to changes more easily if they are introduced gradually and given lots of affection, care, and confidence. They can get used to their new environment if you create a new routine and give them plenty of mental and physical stimulation. Keeping familiar toys or objects in their new setting might also provide them a sense of security and comfort.
Number 3: Unpredictable or inconsistent behavior from their human family.
German Shepherds may become confused and emotionally disturbed by their human family members' inconsistent or unpredictable conduct. Because these dogs depend on their human family for direction and structure, they can get uneasy and uncomfortable when their behavior is erratic or unpredictable. Anxiety, fear, and behavioral issues like violence or destructive conduct might result from this. German Shepherds may develop trust with their human families and learn what is expected of them with consistent training and good reinforcement. German Shepherds can behave well when kept in a steady, predictable setting with defined rules and boundaries. This can give them a sense of security and self-confidence.
Number 4: Ignoring or neglecting them.
A German Shepherd can suffer major emotional repercussions from being neglected or ignored. These dogs are very social creatures who enjoy receiving love and attention from their human families. They may experience feelings of despair, depression, and anxiety when they are ignored or neglected because they may come to believe that they are unloved, unimportant, and undesired. German Shepherds can become destructive or exhibit behavioral issues when left alone for extended periods of time without the right mental and physical activity. It's critical to give German Shepherds the love and care they require because neglecting them can have a long-term negative impact on their health and behavior.
Number 5: Lack of socialization or interaction with other dogs or people.
The emotional health of German Shepherds might suffer from a lack of socialization or interaction with other animals or people. These dogs are extremely sociable and want for companionship with both their human family and other canines. Lack of social interaction can make them lonely, bored, and worried, which can result in aggressive or harmful conduct. German Shepherds can benefit from regular mental and physical activity, socializing with other dogs and people, and other forms of stimulation.
Number 6: Physical or medical neglect.
Neglecting to provide German Shepherds with veterinary treatment, for example, can have substantial and long-lasting effects on their emotional and physical health. German Shepherds can become afraid, anxious, and aggressive when they are in pain or have a medical issue. Neglecting a dog's medical needs can result in serious, potentially fatal conditions as well as a great deal of emotional pain for the animal. Regular veterinary examinations, vaccines, and early medical attention are essential for maintaining the physical and mental health of German Shepherds.

description: When one family dog wandered from the farm they believed that he was lost forever. The dog made his way far away and lived on the streets for years, depending on friendly strangers to look after him. Then he was finally taken to a shelter. He had no interest in humans and showed no emotions. He would take food but did not want love or the people to comfort him. The shelter finally decided to get him a forever home, but they could never have predicted the results! What happened next will blow your mind and bring happy tears to your eyes. This story shows you should never give up hope.

Welcome to Animal Reunion, where bonds are brought to life and hearts are filled with joy.  "
 ‚ÄúIn this series, we witness fascinating stories about animals and their human companions.‚Äù
 In this video, we will watch 30 Animal Reunion videos. Let's get started
________
Welcome to our channel, where heartwarming reunions between animals will melt your heart and restore your faith in the power of love and connection. Witness the incredible moments when animals are reunited with their long-lost companions, families, or human friends. From dogs finding their way back home after years of separation to elephants recognizing their caretakers, our videos capture the emotional journeys of these extraordinary reunions.
If you can't even look at your pet when you leave for work in the morning, then imagine what it must have been like for these people to say goodbye to their animals for much longer...or even forever! They really didn't know if they would ever see them again... But today we're showing moments when all these animals reunited with their owners after years! This video is going to break your heart, but you‚Äôre definitely going to want to subscribe to this channel and get some more!

With a focus on the incredible bond animals share, we bring you captivating stories of resilience, loyalty, and unconditional love. Whether it's a cat reuniting with her kittens, a rescued orangutan finding solace with its newfound family, or a horse joyfully recognizing its human companion, these reunions remind us of the deep emotional intelligence and capacity for affection that animals possess.

description:
Kathleen Degenhardt lives with fibrodysplasia ossificans progressiva (FOP), an ultra-rare connective tissue disorder that turns muscle, tendons, and ligaments to bone. 

For Kathleen, treatment innovation and a tight-knit support community have been instrumental to her living a good life with FOP. Now, Kathleen shares her story in hopes of increasing awareness of the telltale symptoms of this rare disease, and as a means of combatting the isolation of being "rare."

For more information about FOP, including symptoms, diagnosis, treatment, and community support, visit https://www.focusonfop.com/en-ca/.

If you or someone you know is living with FOP, connect with the Canadian FOP Network at http://www.cfopn.org/.
tags: ['FOP', 'Fibrodysplasia Ossificans Progressiva', 'CFOPN', 'Rare Disease', 'Ultra-Rare Disorder']
title: Life in a Body Slowly Turning To Bone: Kathleen‚Äôs Story

description:
00:00 Hello, dear viewers. Get ready for an emotional journey that will touch your hearts and restore your faith in humanity. In today's video, we will witness the incredible abundance of good-hearted people in the world.

00:20 WoW, as the trainer gives a fish to the dolphin and playfully tells it to stop eating. To everyone's surprise, the clever dolphin holds the fish in its mouth and gives it back to the trainer.

01:15 Individuals quietly approach homeless people on the street who are facing difficult circumstances. Without drawing attention, they discreetly drop off food to provide support and nourishment.

01:55 This is teamwork between a man and his four-legged friend! As the man carries a large bag filled with plastic bottles, his loyal dog lends a helping paw by dragging a bag.

02:07 They say that when you seek something, you'll find an opportunity, and this father exemplifies that perfectly. 

02:52 In a moment of misfortune, the fruits in the hands of a young man crossing the road were scattered. However, the kindness of passersby shines through as they pause to help him gather his fallen fruits.

03:45 Sailors came to rescue a seabird stuck in the water with its tail wrapped in wire. With care and gentleness, they worked to save the bird from its plight.

04:25 Firefighters rescued an elderly couple from a dangerous situation, saving their lives.

05:10 [Laugh] when a cat trusts their owner.
 and when a cat doesn‚Äôt 

06:15 In a quack-tastic display of compassion, a police car is on a mission to ensure the safety of our feathered friends. 

08:00 With a feathery friend as a passenger, the journey continues as this colorful companion accompanies the officer on their patrol. It's a comical and unexpected encounter that adds a touch of whimsy to the daily routine.

08:30 These two incredible children have shown their remarkable generosity by sharing their last piece of bread with strangers.

12:00 It's truly remarkable how the eagle responded to the person who approached to offer help. The eagle's lack of resistance showed a sense of trust and recognition of the friendly attitude.

12:30 A man with a broken leg emerged in front of a passing car, seeking assistance. As the driver stopped to help, he saw a girl crying beside an overturned motorcycle. The father, realizing his mistake, embraced his daughter and expressed remorse for his imprudence. The driver safely transported the father and daughter to their home, ensuring they reached their destination with care and support.

14:10 On July 3, 2023, an unusual incident occurred at Crandon amusement park as roller coaster riders found themselves stuck upside down for hours. However, thanks to the prompt action of rescuers, the stranded individuals were safely brought down from the roller coaster.

We're delighted that you enjoyed today's video! If you want to see more amazing content like this, don't forget to hit that subscribe button and join our channel. Stay updated with the latest videos and be part of our wonderful community. Thank you for your support.

description:
Only in theaters December 15. #WonkaMovie

Based on the extraordinary character at the center of Charlie and the Chocolate Factory, Roald Dahl‚Äôs most iconic children‚Äôs book and one of the best-selling children‚Äôs books of all time, ‚ÄúWonka‚Äù tells the wondrous story of how the world‚Äôs greatest inventor, magician and chocolate-maker became the beloved Willy Wonka we know today.

From Paul King, writer/director of the ‚ÄúPaddington‚Äù films, David Heyman, producer of ‚ÄúHarry Potter,‚Äù ‚ÄúGravity,‚Äù ‚ÄúFantastic Beasts‚Äù and ‚ÄúPaddington,‚Äù and producers Alexandra Derbyshire (the ‚ÄúPaddington‚Äù films, ‚ÄúJurassic World: Dominion‚Äù) and Luke Kelly (‚ÄúRoald Dahl‚Äôs The Witches‚Äù), comes an intoxicating mix of magic and music, mayhem and emotion, all told with fabulous heart and humor. Starring Timoth√©e Chalamet in the title role, this irresistibly vivid and inventive big screen spectacle will introduce audiences to a young Willy Wonka, chock-full of ideas and determined to change the world one delectable bite at a time‚Äîproving that the best things in life begin with a dream, and if you‚Äôre lucky enough to meet Willy Wonka, anything is possible.

Starring alongside Chalamet are Calah Lane (‚ÄúThe Day Shall Come‚Äù), Emmy and Peabody Award winner Keegan-Michael Key (‚ÄúThe Prom,‚Äù ‚ÄúSchmigadoon‚Äù), Paterson Joseph (‚ÄúVigil,‚Äù ‚ÄúNoughts + Crosses‚Äù), Matt Lucas (‚ÄúPaddington,‚Äù ‚ÄúLittle Britain‚Äù), Mathew Baynton (‚ÄúThe Wrong Mans,‚Äù ‚ÄúGhosts‚Äù), Oscar nominee Sally Hawkins (‚ÄúThe Shape of Water,‚Äù the ‚ÄúPaddington‚Äù films, ‚ÄúSpencer‚Äù), Rowan Atkinson (the ‚ÄúJohnny English‚Äù and ‚ÄúMr. Bean‚Äù films, ‚ÄúLove Actually‚Äù), Jim Carter (‚ÄúDownton Abbey‚Äù), with Oscar winner Olivia Colman (‚ÄúThe Favourite‚Äù). The film also stars Natasha Rothwell (‚ÄúWhite Lotus,‚Äù ‚ÄúInsecure‚Äù), Rich Fulcher (‚ÄúMarriage Story,‚Äù ‚ÄúDisenchantment‚Äù), Rakhee Thakrar (‚ÄúSex Education,‚Äù ‚ÄúFour Weddings and a Funeral‚Äù), Tom Davis (‚ÄúPaddington 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúKing Gary‚Äù) and Kobna Holdbrook-Smith (‚ÄúPaddington 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúZack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMary Poppins Returns‚Äù).

Simon Farnaby (‚ÄúPaddington 2‚Äù) & Paul King wrote the screenplay, based on a story by King and characters created by Roald Dahl. Michael Siegel, Cate Adams, Rosie Alison and Tim Wellspring are serving as executive producers. King‚Äôs behind-the-scenes creative team includes director of photography Chung-Hoon Chung (‚ÄúLast Night in Soho,‚Äù ‚ÄúAh-ga-ssi‚Äù); Oscar-nominated production designer Nathan Crowley (‚ÄúTenet,‚Äù ‚ÄúDunkirk‚Äù); editor Mark Everson (the ‚ÄúPaddington‚Äù films); Oscar-winning costume designer Lindy Hemming (the ‚ÄúPaddington‚Äù films, ‚ÄúTopsy-Turvy‚Äù); and composer Joby Talbot (the ‚ÄúSing‚Äù films). Neil Hannon of the band The Divine Comedy is writing original songs for the film.

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents, in Association with Village Roadshow Pictures, a Heyday Films Production, a Paul King Confection, ‚ÄúWonka,‚Äù set to open in theaters and in IMAX internationally beginning in December 2023 and in North America on December 15, 2023; it will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.

description:
Hello, my name is Shelby and I am a potter based in Victoria, Australia. 
In this vlog, I spend the last week of preparation creating some pieces for the kiln. I figure out a plan for kiln firings and begin the task of organising and packing up all the pottery for the market. This video could have been two parts but I felt it was a nice look inside the last week of prep and then a look at the market. 

Here is a list of all the brands/ businesses I mentioned in this video (some of these are gifted and some of these I purchased):
1. Whisker Wood Displays: Wooden market displays https://www.etsy.com/au/shop/WhiskerWoodDisplays?
2. Mad Hatter Designs: https://www.etsy.com/au/shop/MadHatterDesignsau?
3. Lindsay Stitches: https://www.lindsaystitches.com

Small biz and brand feature at the end of the video:
1. Baby G Watches: https://casioau.com/collections/baby-g/
2. Merry People Gumboots: https://merrypeople.com
3. Everlasting Collective (book stack): https://www.instagram.com/everlasting_collective_/
4. Chrysanthos Underglaze Chalk and Pencils: https://www.chrysanthos.com
5. Farm Goat Soap: https://farmgoat.com.au
6.  Bendigo Brittle: https://www.bendigobrittle.com.au
7. Hey Laidy (Camera Strap): https://www.etsy.com/au/shop/HeyLaidy
8. Jala Jala Treats:  https://www.jalajalatreats.com.au
9. Chimerical Homewares: https://www.chimericalhomewares.com.au
10. Oak and Thistle (hair clips): https://www.oakandthistledesigns.com
11. Kennedy Smith Candles: https://kennedysmith.com.au
12. Pete Cromer (pet rocks and budgies): https://www.petecromer.com
13. Princess Highway (clothes): https://princesshighway.com.au
14. Fiona Howes (ceramic flowers): https://www.instagram.com/fionahowesceramics/?hl=en
15. Nice Digs (Cat collar): https://www.nicedigs.com.au

Throughout this video I take you behind the scenes of all parts of the process with lots of Timelapse's. The Timelapse's make it a little easier to keep focused on the work at hand whilst being able to show you what I am up too. 

I hope you like these videos as a little something different whilst I prepare and I will have my regular goodness back soon once I get through some of this work!

description:
In the bustling streets of the city, where time hurriedly moved forward, an unforeseen encounter unfolded within the walls of a quaint restaurant. Little did the manager know that this seemingly ordinary day would bring a lesson in humility and compassion that would forever alter the course of his life.

As the sun dipped behind the horizon, casting its warm glow upon the streets, an old woman appeared at the entrance of the establishment. Clad in tattered clothes and bearing the marks of a life full of hardships, she looked like a beggar seeking respite from the world's callousness.

The restaurant manager, engrossed in the demands of his profession, saw her through a lens clouded by the incessant rush of the daily grind. Without a second thought, he approached the woman, his tone laden with impatience, and urged her to leave, assuming she was just another intruder.

Unbeknownst to him, the frail figure before him held a story far beyond her appearance. Little did he realize that her presence in his restaurant was no coincidence. She was a harbinger of a poignant reminder - a reminder that life is an ever-changing tapestry of fates interwoven, and the fortunes of one can swiftly mirror the destitution of another.

The old woman, whose identity remained concealed in the shadow of her humble exterior, bore a valuable lesson that transcended social barriers and the veneer of appearances. Life's uncertainties could cast anyone into the abyss of despair, and the same hands that once pushed others away might one day yearn for the warmth of a helping soul.

In the narrative of existence, compassion and empathy stand as beacons of hope, illuminating the darkest of paths and transforming callous hearts. And as the restaurant manager unknowingly closed the door on the enigmatic old woman, he had yet to learn the profound truth that life's wheel turns without pause, and one must embrace the humanity within, for there lies the key to the transformative power of kindness.

Thus, this seemingly ordinary day would unfurl a tale of awakening - a story that would not only change the manager's perception of others but, more importantly, his perception of himself. For in this intricate dance of life, the way we treat others echoes far beyond the present moment, leaving indelible imprints on the very fabric of our shared journey.

description:
CINCINNATI (WKRC) - A woman collapsed in a Hamilton County courtroom after being sentenced to prison for a car crash.

Michelle Lake pleaded for mercy. While Judge Patrick Dinkelacker said he sympathized, he showed Lake none, calling her a ticking time bomb.

"I'm so very sorry for what happened,‚Äù said Lake during sentencing. ‚ÄúI wish so badly I could take that day back."

But the 35-year-old mother of three cannot take back the 2018 crash that severely injured two people. It was Thursday, Dec. 6 at about 9:30 a.m., when Lake was driving and crossed the center line, hitting a car driven by Jody Cox.

"I still have issues; I still have pain,‚Äù said Cox during the sentencing. ‚ÄúI still can't walk right. I still have emotional issues. I still see that constantly and it affects me a great deal."

"I'm so sorry. I'm so very sorry," said Lake to Cox.

Another adult passenger and Cox's 2-year-old were in the car. Luckily, the 2-year-old wasn't hurt, but the judge reminded Lake that investigators determined cocaine, fentanyl and methadone were in her system at the time of the crash.

"These demons haunt me every day,‚Äù said Lake. ‚ÄúAnd the night before the accident, these demons took advantage of the weak state of mind I was in. The decisions that followed will haunt me and the victim's family and my family forever."

But it wasn't necessarily this accident alone on which the prosecutor based his sentencing recommendation of 10 years.

"She's already been to prison twice,‚Äù said the prosecuting attorney. ‚ÄúShe had another crash frighteningly similar to this. Killed a person and only did two years and she did a burglary that she didn't do very long on."

In the end, Dinkelacker gave the maximum sentence -- 10 years for one count of vehicular assault and one count of aggravated vehicular assault, plus a lifetime driver's license suspension.

As the judge read her sentence, Lake‚Äôs knees buckled and she sobbed as she went to the ground. As she was led from the courtroom to begin her sentence, her husband called after her, saying, ‚ÄúI love you‚Äù amidst Lake sobbing, ‚ÄúOh my God; oh my God.‚Äù

In that 2006 crash referenced by the prosecutor, it was Lake's passenger who died. Again, she had only served two years for that conviction.

In delivering the sentence, the judge said he recognizes Lake was remorseful, but he needs to look out for the safety of the community.
title: Judge sentences driver for second serious crash caused while under the influence

description:
SHE SAID YES...Eventually! You would think a beautiful diamond ring hanging in the center of a glass ornament would be easy to spot... 

Erin and Freddie spent Christmas 2013 in beautiful Colorado with the Braun clan. Little did Erin know, Freddie was smuggling a VERY special present through the airport with him. Erin looks back on the day and laughs, understanding now why Freddie was so tense going through airport security.

Freddie schemed the proposal perfectly, and sincerely surprised not only Erin, but the rest of the witnesses as well. Both the Braun and Hutch kids get an ornament every year for Christmas, so when it came time for Erin to open hers from the Braun's, she thought she knew exactly what she was unwrapping. It was a beautiful hand-decorated glass ornament... with the engagement ring hanging in the middle of it. 

Eventually, she did see the ring and say YES. It was the happiest moment of their lives - so far! We're so happy the big moment was captured so candidly (thanks Max). Enjoy!

description:
In today‚Äôs video 4 Moments The Kings Guard Show an Act Of Kindness! 

Guard plays with a kid [HQ]
corporal pours water in to the mouth of the Queen's Guard #toweroflondon
Surprise: 5 Year Old Fan Meet Queens Guard
Four-year-old boy salutes next to guardsman at Windsor Castle

Hello boys and girls and welcome to a new video. Today I will be showing you times the queens guard showed an act of kindness. As you may know, the guards must stay in a strict character whilst on their shift. They must not be distracted whilst guarding their post. However, sometimes, there are justified times they must break character. Usually, they do this when something bad is happening, but today I thought I would show you some positive clips where they show a great act of kindness whilst on duty, I promise that you will love every clip in this video so be sure to watch till the very end. If you enjoy this video at any moment, be sure to comment, like and share to friends and family.
This video comes all the way over from Stockholm, the capital city of Sweden. Straight away you see a Swedish royal guard outside the royal castle. After a few moments, a small kid walks in the view of the camera. He is holding an umbrella and wearing a hat. Basically, he is trying to imitate the guard Infront of him. He walks up to the guard, brings his umbrella to his side of his body and starts marching up and down. You can tell he is really loving the situation. After a while the guard joins in with the boy and they march in synchronization. It is such a great video, and I guarantee it made the boys day!
This next video shows a king‚Äôs guard protecting his area at the tower of London. If you did not know, the kings guard are not able to drink or go to the toilet whilst on duty. They must get on with the shift without leaving their post. There are sometimes exceptions, in this instance it was a hot summers day and they need to hydrate. This is where the corporal comes over and helps the guard drink water. A great show of kindness.
This is a brilliant video and I am sure you will absolutely love it. This is recorded by Buckingham Palace; a little kid is dressed in a full king‚Äôs guard outfit. He looks so cool. There is a guard and a police officer talking in the distance, whilst this is happening, the kid is saluting the guard. All of a sudden, the guard walks out of Buckingham palace and visits the young boy, starts shacking his hand and takes a photo with him. I am pretty sure this is against protocol, nevertheless it is a classic video and the kid must be so happy by this moment.
I am sure you have seen this video before; it is a goldmine of a video. Scott the boy in this video was celebrating his birthday, so decided to dress up in the king‚Äôs guard outfit and visit the guards at the tower of London. Soon after, a group of kings guards are marching towards a building, I assume they have finished the shift. They march past him as he salutes to them all. One decides to go back to the kid, tells him to walk over, they stand side-by-side as his mother takes a photo with them together.

description:
In the tapestry of life, there are few moments as precious and heartwarming as when grandparents meet their grandchild for the very first time. Their reactions vary from the dramatic to the tender, showcasing a range of emotions that speak volumes about the extraordinary bond that is about to unfold.

In a heartwarming moment, the family gathers, creating a surprise for their beloved granddad. As he meets his newborn grandchild, tears of joy stream down his face, capturing the profound emotions of love and connection. In this cherished reunion, the power of family and the beauty of new beginnings come together, creating memories that will last a lifetime

Grandparents meet their grandchild and think, 'Wow, our hearts are full!' But wait, there's more! Their sneaky son unveils the surprise‚Äîa hidden twin grandchild! Cue the double take, the jaw drop, and the hilarious speechless moment.

Imagine their joy, after months of quarantine, when the dream finally comes true. Grandparents meet their grandchild for the very first time, and hearts instantly melt. It's a moment filled with love, laughter, and the realization that dreams really do come true.

Despite health challenges, Granddad sprints up the stairs to meet his long-awaited grandchild. Love knows no bounds, and he's determined to embrace the joy that awaits.

Unbeknownst to the grandparents, their daughter planned a surprise visit, bringing along their grandchild. As the door swung open, their jaws dropped in astonishment and delight. Tears of joy flowed freely as they held their grandchild for the very first time, creating a cherished memory they never expected.

Across the miles, separated by distance and quarantine restrictions, the grandparents yearned to meet their 3-year-old grandchild. Finally, the day arrived when travel became possible. As they embraced, their hearts swelled with love and excitement, creating an instant bond that transcended the time they had missed.

In a hilarious twist, the mischievous baby decided to take matters into their own tiny hands. Crawling with determination, they made their way to their grandparents' doorstep, leaving their parents in disbelief. When the door swung open, laughter erupted as the surprised grandparents found themselves face-to-face with their adventurous grandbaby, who had orchestrated the most adorable surprise visit.

As the grandchild dashed through the garden, her pigtails bouncing with each step, she carried a secret mission in her little heart: to surprise her beloved grandparents.When that little whirlwind of energy bolts towards their eagerly awaiting grandparents, it's like witnessing a superhero sprint to their secret lair. The excitement is contagious, and the bond that forms in that very moment becomes the stuff of legends. 


As our heartwarming journey concludes, let's celebrate the incredible influence grandparents have on their grandchildren. From sharing wisdom and traditions to showering love and support, they play an irreplaceable role in shaping their grandkids' lives. So, let's treasure these special moments, for the bond between grandparents and grandchildren is a lifelong source of joy and inspiration.

The Atlantic Coast Conference (ACC) is a collegiate athletic conference in the United States in which its fifteen member universities compete in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA's) Division I, with its football teams competing in the Football Bowl Subdivision (FBS), the highest levels for athletic competition in US-based collegiate sports. The ACC sponsors competition in twenty-five sports with many of its member institutions' athletic programs held in high regard nationally. ACC teams and athletes have claimed dozens of national championships in multiple sports throughout the conference's history. Generally, the ACC's top athletes and teams in any particular sport in a given year are considered to be among the top collegiate competitors in the nation. The ACC is considered to be one of the six collegiate power conferences, all of which enjoy extensive media coverage and automatic qualifying for their football champion into the Bowl Championship Series (BCS). With the advent of the College Football Playoff in 2014, the ACC will be one of five conferences with a contractual tie-in to an "access bowl", the successors to the BCS. 

Founded in 1953 in Greensboro, North Carolina, by seven universities located in the South Atlantic States, the conference added additional members in late 1953, 1979, 1991, 2004, and 2013. The 2004 and 2013 additions extended the conference's footprint into the Northeast and Midwest. The most recent expansion in 2013 saw the additions of the University of Notre Dame, the University of Pittsburgh, and Syracuse University. In 2012, the University of Maryland's Board of Regents voted to withdraw from the ACC to join the Big Ten Conference. On November 28, 2012, the ACC's Council of Presidents voted unanimously to invite the University of Louisville as a full member, replacing Maryland.

description:
Award-winning hotelier Alex Polizzi visits a derelict 15-bedroom Blackpool hotel, The New Lyngarth, which is very much down in the dumps. But in her quest to get the owner to reach for the stars, will The New Lyngarth end up in the gutter? Subscribe to Our Taste: https://bit.ly/3OZoDcV

Series 8 - Episode 8 | This film was first broadcast: 2011

The Hotel Inspector meets 49-year-old Andrew Brown, who took over the derelict 15-bedroom hotel, The New Lyngarth, in 2009. But after splashing out ¬£250,000 on renovations, his Blackpool establishment is still very much down in the dumps. Andrew has grand plans for his seaside hotel. But with dodgy decor, no star rating, zero profits and questionable cleanliness, all the hotel has managed to attract so far is bad reviews. And when water drips on Alex's head during breakfast, the full extent of the hotel's problems begins to unfold. The award-winning hotelier hopes to turn things around by bringing the hotel up to the scratch and getting The New Lyngarth an accreditation from Visit England. But in her quest to get Andrew to reach for the stars, will The New Lyngarth end up in the gutter?

description:
Dramatic footage captures the moment a cow fell from a lorry into busy traffic on the M6.

The animal dropped onto the inside lane of the road at around 10am on Tuesday 1 August.

It can be seen skidding towards oncoming traffic, forcing drivers to take evasive action.

Police say another cow also broke free two miles away, and the motorway was closed for around 90 minutes between junctions seven and 10.

The cows were left injured according to the Central Motorway Police Group.

Kevin Rogers witnesses the bizarre incident unfold in front of him.

‚ÄúThe cow fell out the bottom of the lorry," he said.

‚ÄúI was the first car coming head-on to it and I managed to miss it."

description:
A woman has been arrested after a motorcyclist was killed in a shooting near 67th Avenue and Thunderbird Road.  The motorcyclist, identified as a 23-year-old man, had an apparent gunshot wound. He was taken to a hospital where he died. During the initial investigation, police determined the shooting stemmed from a road rage incident near 67th Avenue and Greenway Road, involving the motorcyclist and occupants of a silver passenger car. On Friday, police announced that a 21-year-old woman was arrested in connection to the shooting. Officials say she was a passenger in the vehicle at the time of the incident.

More on the shooting: https://www.abc15.com/traffic/motorcyclist-hospitalized-after-shooting-near-67th-avenue-and-thunderbird

description:
A young girl was rescued this week from inside a well by the Syrian Civil Defence AKA the "White Helmets" in Aleppo, Syria, after falling down it while playing near her home.

Video said to be in Al Bab City shows Assaf al Assaf, a member of the Syrian Civil Defence, Aleppo branch, being lowered inside the well and footage from his onboard camera showing the dramatic rescue in action.

Four-year-old Sumaiah cried out for her mother, as al Assaf tries to calm her and asks to see if her hand is hurt, before the pair are brought up to safety. The little girl asks for her doll during the rescue.

The incident is said to have taken place at 3 p.m. local time and the rescue operation took one hour, according to the White Helmets.

Sumaiah is now fine and was not injured, they added.

description:
Cases like Brandon Mateo‚Äôs are becoming all too familiar for law enforcement officers.

According to the Washoe County Regional Medical Examiner‚Äôs Office they identified a total 192 deaths by suicide in 2019 ‚Äì six of which were minors 17-years-old and younger. In 2020 ‚Äì there were 183 suicides throughout the region ‚Äì two were minors. 

So far this year, preliminary findings (meaning ‚Äì the deaths could still be under investigation) the Medical Examiner has identified 52 suicides. Four by people 17-years-old and younger.

The Washoe County Sheriff‚Äôs Office sends detectives to investigate suicides to ensure there has been no crime. More than a dozen WCSO personnel worked Brandon‚Äôs case from Patrol and Detectives. All have been affected by this one event.  All continue to work at the Washoe County Sheriff‚Äôs Office as first responders.

description:
** (Disclaimer: Video posted strictly for educational and information purposes only) **
Newly released video shows the arrest of a man and his transgender lover after the pair allegedly kidnapped a woman. Authorities say they were planning to take her to a cave and brainwash her into marrying one of them. When police found her back in January, she was chained down by the neck in the back of a minivan in New Mexico. The woman was rescued less than 24 hours after witnesses saw the her being dragged out of her Las Vegas, Nevada apartment. After receiving an alert, police pulled over the van and arrested her ex-boyfriend, and his new lover.

Police then found the kidnapped woman in the car and unchained her. ‚ÄúHe dragged me out of the place, and I fought so (bleep) hard cause I was like, this is how you die,‚Äù she said. In a federal criminal complaint, investigators say the suspects planned the kidnapping for more than a year. Throughout the arrest, One of the suspect was singing the words to the hymn ‚ÄúAmazing Grace,‚Äù asked for his bibles, and made some mental notes. ‚ÄúNote to self‚Ä¶ Wear shoes next time,‚Äù Suspect said. Both Suspects face charges of kidnapping, false imprisonment, and conspiracy.

description:
Donald Trump has claimed that his arraignment in Washington DC was a "persecution" shortly after leaving court.

Mr Trump falsely claimed "When you look at what is happening, this is a persecution of a political opponent, this was never supposed to happen in America," from the steps of his private plane.

The Department of Justice has repeatedly stated that its criminal investigation is independent of the White House and the political apparatus of the government.

The former president then went on to claim that he has a "substantial" lead in both the Republican primary and against Joe Biden.

He also falsely stated: "This is the persecution of the person that is leading by very, very substantial numbers in the Republican primary and leading Biden by a lot. If you can't beat him, you persecute him or you prosecute him, you can't let this happen in America."

The first New York Times poll of the 2024 election cycle shows a dead heat between President Biden and Donald Trump

A recent poll from FiveThirtyEight has Mr Trump ahead of his rival Ron DeSantis in the GOP primary.

description:
Hundreds of pro-coup demonstrators gathered in Niger's capital, Niamey, on Thursday, denouncing sanctions imposed on the country's new military regime by Ecowas, west Africa's regional bloc led by Nigeria. The march fell on the 63rd anniversary of Niger's independence from France. Demonstrators gathered around Independence Square in Niamey where they chanted anti-France and anti-western slogans. 
 
Tensions have been simmering between Niger's ruling junta and its neighbours in the Ecowas bloc, as calls to restore the ousted president, Mohamed Bazoum, face resistance in Niger. Gen Abdourahamane Tchiani, head of the new government rejected sanctions, warning against interference in Niger's internal affairs. 'The National Council for Safeguarding the Homeland rejects all sanctions and refuses to yield to any threat, wherever it may come from,' said Tchiani on Wednesday during a televised address. France and Italy have begun evacuating their citizens from Niger.

description:
Fighters from Russia's private Wagner mercenary force are being moved close to NATO's eastern flank to destabilize the military alliance, Poland's prime minister said on Thursday (August 3).

Wagner soldiers have begun training with the Belarus national army, prompting Poland to start moving more than 1,000 troops closer to the border. On Tuesday it accused Belarus of violating its airspace with military helicopters.

"We have to be aware that the number of these provocations will increase," Mateusz Morawiecki said after meeting Lithuanian President Gitanas Nauseda in eastern Poland.

"This is what the operational activities on their side are about. In order to destabilise. In order to create unrest, chaos, uncertainty," he added.

The politicians met in the Suwalki Gap, a sparsely populated but strategically important area of Polish territory between Belarus and the Russian exclave of Kaliningrad that joins the Baltic states to other NATO members.

Nauseda said the number of Wagner fighters in Belarus could be higher than 4,000.

Belarus allowed Russian President Vladimir Putin to use its territory as a launch pad for the Ukraine invasion, but has not committed its own troops to the war.

This four-year-old girl from Armenia had surgery in November, and on December 27, 2019 the implant was ‚Äúswitched on.‚Äù  For the first time this beautiful child was able to hear her parents‚Äô voices! 
The organization that made her cochlear implant surgery possible is the Armenian International Medical Fund (AIM Fund), and we will continue giving the gift of cochlear implants to hearing-impaired children in Armenia. If you wish to learn more about the Fund, please visit www.armenianimf.org, www.facebook.com/aim.fund or 
e-mail us at aimf.donate@gmail.com

description: For this you will need approx. 7 feet of 1 1/2" ribbon and flexible floral wire. I prefer 20 gauge floral wire for all my bows. Fold your ribbon at 6" making 6 complete loops. Starting at the  middle of the loops cut inward 1/3 of the ribbon width on a slight angle. Wrap a 8" strip of wire around the ribbon and twist one turn. Cut ribbon for the streamers and attach to the bow.

description:
An overview of 2 major life events for Michael Williams, at age 3 being diagnosed with leukemia and age 31 an auto accident crushing his skull, to the prosthetic and the healing and restoration process of the Lord through it all.
Follow his progress and what he‚Äôs doing now on Facebook @WilliamsTribeMikesMiracles
https://www.facebook.com/WilliamsTribeMikesMiracles/

We have also started a Support and Social Group for Martin and N. Palm Beach counties. For more information check out our upcoming events in the Events tab on our Facebook page.
https://www.facebook.com/WilliamsTribeMikesMiracles/

If you would like to donate to help cover the cost of these much needed Social and Support activities for the group, you can donate here to help them. There is no insurance to cover this much needed part of people‚Äôs health and healing process. All donations are greatly appreciated because many have no form of income for many months, even years while waiting for disability approval and are unable to pay anything. Please use the link below and in MENU choose Donations. Thank you! 

https://thewilliamstribe.wordpress.com/

Donations at this time are made to Sandra Williams and will be used toward helping support the needs of the group and put programs in place to benefit the group. We do not have 501(c)(3) status at this time but are hoping to have it in place soon. Thank you!

I'll show you how to organize a small kitchen, a small laundry room, a small bathroom, a small refrigerator, and a small closet! 

These creative space-saving hacks will help you maximize the space you have! I hope these quick organization ideas help you organize your home in no time! Enjoy!

description:
Sometimes, my go-to method of deck cleaning (https://youtu.be/pmw-n86WoxM) isn't the best choice.  For example, when cleaning in cold weather, oxygen bleach doesn't work so well.

In this video, I show a quick and cheap method of making a solution of sodium hydroxide for use in cleaning grimy wooden decks in cold weather.  

Do your homework and unstained the chemical well BEFORE you use it.  Sodium hydroxide can be very dangerous! 

Yes, after cleaning a wooden deck with sodium hydroxide, it's a fine idea to treat it all with oxalic acid to brighten the wood.  I illustrate that here: https://youtu.be/ycRlpkWVLTE

This video here is a basic HOW TO... sort of like "Deck Cleaning 102."  As any professional exterior cleaner or deck restorer knows, *much* more can be said and done about cleaning a wood deck, but I hope this video answers the most basic questions.

For those wondering where to buy the chemical used in this video, you can click the link below.  Note that I earn a small commission if you purchase the product by this link:

ABOUT PREFERRED COATING SOLUTIONS
With a combined ten years of experience in sealcoating, hardscaping, power washing, and epoxy services, Preferred Coating Solutions positively transforms the lives of investment-conscious homeowners by protecting, prolonging, and enhancing their exterior and interior surfaces, so they can spend more time enjoying these spaces, and waste less time working on their homes themselves.

SERVICE AREA
Preferred Coating Solutions services the Southwestern Ontario area, in Windsor, Tecumseh, LaSalle, Amherstburg, Belle River, Lakeshore Leamington, McGregor, Harrow, Essex, Chatham and Essex County. 

VIDEO NOTES
Joe introduces today's sitewalk: a front porch epoxy. We see a Preferred employee grinding down the porch surface to provide a clean slate for the polyaspartic coating to be applied to. Joe talks about the main issues the client was facing. Their porch had cracked in multiple spots, and lacked the curb appeal the home owner desired. Joe introduces the solution to this problem. A beige polyaspartic coating will be used on the cement, with greyscale  coloured flakes to match the brick surrounding the front entrance. Polyaspartic coatings have UV protection and will protect the cement underneath from cracking, wear, and stains. We see joe spread and roll the polyaspartic coating onto the porch. He then proceeds to toss the flakes to cover the porch. After 2 hours, they scrape off and collect the excess flakes. Then, they apply a clear coat to the flakes to cure over 24 hours. The next day, Joe comes back to check how the job turned out. We see before and after photos. Joe does his outro and leaves.

With a combined ten years of experience in sealcoating, hardscaping, power washing, and epoxy services, Preferred Coating Solutions positively transforms the lives of investment-conscious homeowners by protecting, prolonging, and enhancing their exterior and interior surfaces, so they can spend more time enjoying these spaces, and waste less time working on their homes themselves.

SERVICE AREA
Preferred Coating Solutions services the Southwestern Ontario area, in Windsor, Tecumseh, LaSalle, Amherstburg, Belle River, Lakeshore Leamington, McGregor, Harrow, Essex, Chatham and Essex County. 

VIDEO NOTES
Joe introduces today's sitewalk: applying epoxy to his grandparents' porch! He shows that the porch has damage to the concrete and is in need of a new coating. Joe explains that the most important things to do for this job are to repair the concrete, and to make sure the porch is slip resistant and safe to use. He says that porch epoxy is perfect for the type of client who knows exactly what they want because of the amount of styles epoxy can come in. 

Joe and Evan get to work on applying the first coat of epoxy, as well as the flakes. You see Evan applying epoxy to the side of the porch using a paint brush, while Joe uses a roller to do the main application to the porch and steps. Joe then begins to toss flakes all over the epoxy. All of this is done within a time limit of 40 minutes. The epoxy must cure for 8-12 hours. So Joe and Evan leave the site and will come back the next day to continue.

Joe and Evan come back the next day to continue the porch epoxy. Joe scrapes away excess flakes to create a flat, even surface. Evan cleans up extra flakes using a special vacuum. Joe mixes in Silica sand with the clear epoxy to make it slip resistant. This is important for clients who are elderly to ensure their epoxy surfaces are safe.

We watch Joe and Evan apply the clear coat of epoxy mixed with silica sand in a similar fashion as the first oat application. They leave and await the final results on the final day. The difference in before ad after is shown, and you can see for yourself, that this porch has been transformed to look incredible, is safer to use, and is now protected by epoxy from future wear and tear.

description:
Visit our website:
www.dependableconcrete.com
215-821-9779

My company, Dependable Concrete LLC,  was hired to replace this damaged and unsafe walkway with a new concrete walkway, and in this short video I will demonstrate to you step by step  how I completed this job. 

After demoing the concrete we replace the vent water or gas covers. 
These vents were missing covers and were clogged with soil and trash. 

For the right fit, i prefer using a 4‚Äù flex hose

For durability,  I prefer using air entrained 4000psi concrete integrated with fiber mesh 

It‚Äôs important to protect the plumbing covers from the wet concrete

To level the walkway,  I screed the concrete using  a long 2x4 straight edge 

For jointing, I prefer to snap a chalk line as a guide to guarantee a straight line when installing A long joint

At the first stage of finishing the concrete I apply our joint lines using  a bull-float jointer along with a 2x4 as a guide for straight joint lines .

Once the concrete is poured, I begin the process of removing the protect wrapping and setting the vent covers flush with the concrete.

After the concrete has dried enough to prevent deep impressions, , I begin the second stage of finishing.  Which includes applying tools for jointing, troweling and edging. 


At the final stage of finishing the I begin texturing the concrete with a broom finish.

With a finisher ahead troweling the concrete,  another finisher is behind applying the broom finish.
   

Concrete dries very quickly so it's important to be efficient
A broom finish is the ideal finish to prevent slip and falls. A broom finish also provides an even and uniformed look to the concrete. 


The more time you allow the concrete to dry the less aggressive will be brush marks from the bristles

For driveways and inclines, you would broom sooner for an aggressive finish  

Its important to prepare the surface for a broom finish, the surface must be free of holes or trowel marks, the broom will not completely remove these marks.  For a professional looking job, straight broom lines  should be the final look. 

We fine tune the plumbing caps the sit flush with the concrete.  

When brooming concrete, the bristles collect cement, therefore, it's important to continuously clean the bristles with water. A broom loaded with cement leaves trails of cement when pulling the broom across the surface.

Clean bristles will give the job a clean and professional finish.  

Please like, share and subscribe to Dependable Concrete‚Äôs channel this will allow me to inform you on the products we used to complete this project. I immediately respond to all  questions and  comments so leave a question our comment below.

description:
many of you may have questioned why I have slowed down on making videos and its for a collection of reasons like large life changes and spreading myself thin but this without a doubt played a big part in it. I feel like this event should have been no big deal as it is very natural but it was the event that pushed me over the edge. I have been depressed for months and while I embrace moments in my life where i become depressed because i know that i will grow stronger as a person because of it, its also a reason big reason for me to be silent and reflect on life and what is going on around me. A very big part of this channel is the voice over and if I am not in the right mental space just expect me to back away when needed. I feel that is for the greater good. Healing is an ugly process and I don't want to say anything that will create a negative seed in someone else's life. 

All that said the last few months have been such an awesome thing for me and have allowed me to start breaking out of my BS. I was able to giveaway a brand new mower away in Louisville KY and then spent 2 weeks working (something that I love to do) everyday doing power washing in Arkansas from there I came home and lawns were starting to wake up so I got to cut some grass....something I love to do. lol then I got a call from my friend Al in Florida and he asked me to come down and cut some properties with him so I took the family down to Florida for a week. I knocked out a bunch of work then spent a few day at the beach with my wife and daughter jumping waves in the Ocean. On top of all of that we found out that Rachel is pregnant and we are expecting out second child. We are super excited for our new addition to the family in November. 

Thank you so much for you kindess, love and support!!

description:
The options? (1) remove and replace the sunken and cracked concrete pad for an estimated cost of $6,000 (I got three estimates), (2) lift the broken pads at a cost of $2,500, (3) do nothing and hope that no one gets injured. Easy decision, don't you think?

Why repair? (1) Prevent possible injury from tripping, (2) stop the continued sinking and cracking of the concrete pads, and (3) improve the look of the driveway. 

I had tripped on the raised edge separating two concrete driveway pads while getting out of the car several times since we purchased this 40-year-old house, and I was concerned for the safety of myself, my wife, our friends, visitors and elderly members of our family (my father is 94).

description:
#Stampedconcrete #ConcretePatio #EverythingAboutConcrete

In this video I'm going to show you how to form, pour and stamp a concrete patio slab.

This is a backyard concrete patio that will look like Ashlar Slate when we are done stamping the concrete.

First, I show you how to build the forms for the slab. This includes measuring the lengths, screwing them together, squaring the forms and staking them in place. 

I'm also using my Topcon HL5-B self leveling laser level to set the forms to grade/ This is the easiest laser level to use for this kind of work in my opinion.

Second, I show you how to pour the concrete for the patio slab. We spread out the concrete, mag float our edges and screed it level off the tops of the forms. Then I bull float the concrete to smoothen the surface and prepare it for stamping.

Third, I show you how to stamp the concrete using my Ashlar slate stamps. These stamps go together kinda like a puzzle, they have to go in a specific direction and inter-connect or the pattern will not come out right.

Forth, I show you how I saw cut expansion joints and power wash the concrete to prepare it for sealing.

Fifth, I show you what concrete sealer I like  to use on my stamped concrete jobs and how to apply it.

Common Tools / Materials for finishing concrete:
This info is provided from wagnermeters.com

Mixers:
Whether you‚Äôre mixing in a truck, a portable mixer or a wheelbarrow, you want to be sure your concrete is thoroughly mixed for maximum strength and durability.

Wheelbarrows
Ideal for transporting (or even mixing) small batches of concrete or tools on the job site.

Rubber Boots or Work Boots
Concrete is stiff stuff, and wearing waterproof boots is the best way to get through it and prevent contact with your skin. It‚Äôs also easy to rinse your footwear after the concrete is down.

Compactors
If the site of the concrete slab is to be prepped with a sub-base of any type, a compactor helps settle the stone or aggregate into position.

Levels
Both the sub-base and slab surface must be level. A standard long-line level, or a laser level, will let you verify that the slab is completely according to spec before pouring and after.

Tape Measures
Concrete forms and slab depth need the same ‚Äúmeasure twice, pour once‚Äù verification as any other material on the job site. 

Saws
Reciprocating saws, circular saws or grinders can be necessary to cut rebar or forms on the job site. They can also be necessary if a problem develops under the slab and a portion of the concrete has to be removed after it has set and dried.

Shovels
Shovels help distribute concrete around the job site to fill in gaps left during the pouring process or for smaller applications. Square-ended shovels generally work better for concrete; rounded ones spread concrete unevenly.

Rakes and Come-Along Rakes
Using a rake is the quickest way to begin getting the freshly-poured concrete spread more uniformly into place. Garden rakes work but concrete rakes, also called come-along rakes, have a more scooped blade for more easily pre-leveling new concrete. Concrete rakes also have a tine on the back of the blade to help lift rebar or mesh into position before the concrete begins to harden.

Vibrators
Concrete vibrators help release trapped air pockets and excess water from the concrete mix to prevent possibly compromising problems in medium to high slump concrete.

Screeds
Screeds come in a variety of sizes and can be a specific tool (also called straight edges or bump cutters), or can be simple flat pieces of dimensional lumber. The purpose of a screed is to smooth concrete after it has been moved into place by scraping away any excess from the slab surface.

Bull Floats
Bull floats are wide-bladed tools on a long (possibly telescoping handle) that provide the first pass for leveling ridges and filling voids in the concrete after the screed work has been done.

Magnesium Floats
Magnesium floats (or mag floats) are smaller handheld floats typically used to float slab edges or to use for finish work on smaller slabs.
Kneeling Boards
For hand troweling work especially, kneeling boards provide a smooth way to support your weight on the wet concrete while moving easily along the slab surface.

Leveling Concrete Trowels
Trowels also help smooth concrete surfaces for their finish coats before being left to dry. Hand-troweling is common for smaller slabs, or power trowels are often preferred for large slabs. There are varying types of trowels for specific concrete work.

Float Blades and Troweling Blades
A variety of blade types is available for floats and power trowels, each designed to accomplish different finishes. Some care must be taken during the troweling stage not to burnish the surface and prolong drying time.

Groove Cutter/Jointer Tool
For certain job types, grooving the surface also helps prevent cracking or excess damage from shrinkage as the concrete dries or during use.

Edger
An edger is a tool designed to round exposed concrete edges for a smooth finish.

#EverythingAboutConcrete #MikeDayConcrete #Perfectslabforms
The homeowner, Jim Weymouth, formed up this concrete slab and did a great job. The forms were square, straight, staked in place, and set to grade with perfection.
It's rare a homeowner can form a concrete slab this good. We form most the slabs we pour, but occasionally the owner will get the slab ready and we'll just come to pour and finish the concrete.
When Jim forms up a slab, we know from past experience, the slab will be ready to go with nothing for us to adjust or change.

description:
Hello and welcome if you are new! Merry Christmas in July! ;)

Thank you for joining me today for my first Thrift with me and haul for Christmas decor in July video. Since Christmas is my favourite time of the year I can not pass up beautiful unique holiday decor, it just calls my name. I have been collecting these holiday items well before Christmas last year and had to share with you.

So I'm taking you along with me on my many thrifting adventures shopping for Christmas decor and then sharing a huge thrift haul where you will also find some styling ideas. 

Please consider subscribing and sharing with your friends, I would love it if you would join my growing YouTube family. 

Hope you enjoy and feel inspired to start thrifting for your Christmas season.

Thank you for watching. 
xoxo Diana

description:
The moment when soldiers, who have bravely served their country, are finally reunited with their families. The emotions run high as they shed their military roles and embrace their roles as spouses, parents, and children once again.

 A captivating surprise as a military husband returns after a long absence, clutching a bouquet of vibrant flowers. His wife, unaware of his arrival, is about to experience an overwhelming mix of shock and uncontainable joy. 

 When you are back from the Army after serving for the nation the first man you want to see is your father. This soldier is finally got home and can reunite with the family, and purely you can see how much doeshid dad loves him.

  Military father surprises his daughter by coming to school. A regular day at school turns out to be one of the sweetest days for her and according to her reaction surprise is perfect .

  In the spirit of Christmas and armed with an abundance of love, a military daughter hatches a brilliant plan to surprise her parents. It's the middle of the night, and the parents are asleep, unaware of the heartwarming surprise and even her father's near 'heart-stopping' reaction takes an unexpected twist.

  After months of being deployed, a sister returns home to create a magical moment for her unsuspecting sibling. The kitchen becomes the backdrop for an incredible reunion as emotions run high.

  As the cold winter wind blows, a heartwarming reunion unfolds, thawing even the frostiest of days. In this poignant moment, a mother and her military daughter are finally reunited after a long and arduous separation.

 These two brothers embraced, tears of joy streamed down their faces, a testament to the immeasurable love and resilience of siblinghood. The football dinner transformed into a celebration of their reunion, with teammates and friends joining in the jubilation. 

 In the midst of their busy shifts in the cafe kitchen, two brothers receive an unexpected surprise that will change their day and their lives. Their long-awaited military sibling makes a surprise appearance, filling the room with shock, joy. 

 This girl‚Äôs heart filled with a mix of excitement and anticipation. In a heartwarming twist, her mother and sister appear, adorned in their military uniforms, standing proudly by her side, the shock and joy on her face are indescribable.

  While the son and father soak in the precious moments together, their shared laughter and heartfelt conversations fill the air with a sense of gratitude and renewed closeness. The surprise visit becomes a cherished memory for them.

  In a moment filled with tears of joy and overwhelming emotions, a mother and sister are finally reunited with their beloved military son and sister. Their tears speak volumes, expressing the depth of their happiness.

  Her friends sit in conversation, laughter dancing in the air, their eyes widen in disbelief. In that split second, time seems to freeze as they lock gazes with their beloved soldier friend standing before them.

  With a joyful and mischievous smile, the son awaits his mother's reaction. And as she turns around, her eyes widen with disbelief and delight. 

 A father is enjoying his dinner receives a surprise massage that turns out to be his son returning from deployment. Laughter fills the air as tears of joy flow, creating an unforgettable moment of reunion and love.

  A moment that breaks the stillness of the air, a sudden scream erupts as a mother lays eyes on her son, a sailor returning from service. The sheer happiness and excitement on her face is undeniable.

  There is something truly priceless about the feeling of being eagerly awaited at home. As this soldier girl steps through the door, greeted with open arms and radiant smiles, her heart fills with warmth and gratitude.

  Following a long-awaited return, this soldier girl decides to sprinkle her homecoming with a delightful surprise for her beloved sister. Finding her in the bathroom, the sister stumbles upon this unexpected spectacle, her face lights up with sheer shock and joy
#respect #reunion #reaction #emotional #soldiers

description:
A record amount of people attended our K-9 Service Dog Memorial Tuesday, March 7 to pay tribute to K-9 heroes placed in our Garden of Heroes. K9 service dogs and their handlers from many area police and sheriff‚Äôs departments including the Clearwater Police Department and the Pinellas County Sheriff‚Äôs Office were in attendance at the service to remember deceased service dogs from both agencies. Over 80 K-9 service dogs are currently interred at Curlew Hills Memory Gardens. 

Curlew Hills Memory Gardens features one of Florida‚Äôs only authentic pet cemeteries. The company proudly donates burial plots in the pet cemetery to all service animals of both law enforcement agencies. Without this donation, the handler would pay out of his own pocket for the burial of the animal upon his death.

description:
BRANSON, Mo. ‚Äì A local soldier surprises his mom for Mother‚Äôs Day.¬†¬†

‚ÄúI'm here today to surprise my mom,‚Äù Andy¬†Bleil, a specialist with the¬†935th¬†ASB out of¬†Springfield,¬†said. ‚ÄúI just came home from being overseas so¬†‚ÄúI‚Äôm¬†going to see my mom today.¬†I‚Äôm pretty happy about it."¬†

Bleil¬†was stationed in Kuwait with the Army. He says he‚Äôs been gone a year, total, and it‚Äôs been a long time since he‚Äôs seen his mom in person.¬†¬†

The plan to surprise his mom, Mary Beth Gunter, was to have her come to work thinking she‚Äôd be picking out some fabrics for the bank she works at.¬†¬†

That‚Äôs where¬†Bleil¬†would be waiting for her.¬†¬†

"We wanted to surprise her,‚Äù¬†Bleil¬†said. ‚ÄúCatch her off guard."¬†

The rest of the family was also there awaiting Gunter‚Äôs arrival.¬†¬†¬†

"She's going¬†to¬†freak out.,‚Äù said¬†Bleil. ‚ÄúMight be a couple of tears."¬†

Gunter walked through double doors to find¬†Bleil¬†standing there in uniform. Tears were streaming down her face.¬†¬†

‚ÄúHi Momma,‚Äù¬†Bleil¬†said. "Happy Mother's Day...I love you."¬†

Gunter says this was the best Mother‚Äôs Day.¬†

"I'm overwhelmed...completely overwhelmed,‚Äù said Gunter.¬†‚ÄúThis totally surprised me. I had no idea that he was going to be home. I was expecting him next week.¬†

‚ÄúYou just made the best Mother's Day ever¬†ever¬†ever¬†ever¬†ever.‚Äù¬†

Bleil¬†says he‚Äôll be home for a while now.¬†¬†

"Obviously,¬†I've missed all my people, my friends and family, home-cooked meals - that's been a big thing, indoor plumbing,"¬†said¬†Bleil.¬†

Gunter says she‚Äôs just happy he‚Äôs home safe.¬†¬†

"I just want him to eat and relax and hang out with his friends and just be close by,‚Äù Gunter said. ‚ÄúYou don't realize how much you miss somebody until they're¬†gone,¬†and you can't see them.¬†

‚ÄúI feel for all the moms out there who don't have their kids home this Mother's Day. I have such respect for military families."¬†

At the surprise,¬†Bleil‚Äôs¬†family said they only had one day to put it together.
